ed as a Supply support problem.</p>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_249\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"213\"]<a href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/lss_index.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-249 size-full\" src=\"http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/lss_index.jpg\" alt=\"Keeping ships ready since 1980\" width=\"213\" height=\"142\" /></a> Keeping ships ready since 1980[/caption]\r\n\r\n<p>Most of our Maintenance Support Group technicians are former Navy technicians who have extensive experience in the operation and maintenance of the full spectrum of shipboard systems. They are trained onour own in-house lifecycle support management training program developed from years of hands-on experience in all facets of the integrated logistics support system.</p>\r\n<p>The end result is an experienced shipboard maintenance technician who is also trained to troubleshoot and repair any element of the Navys integrated logistics support system to make sure the ILS system provides our sailors with the parts, data and tools they need to restore failed systems with minimal delay.</p>\r\n<h3><a title=\"Maintenance and Supportability Analysis\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/services/integrated-logistics-support/maintenance-and-supportability-analysis/\">Maintenance &amp; Supportability Analysis</a></h3>\r\n<p>ATS has provided preventative and corrective maintenance support solutions to its customers for over 30 years. Analyzing system failures, maintenance actions and technical data that drive logistics support solutions.</p>\r\n<h3><a title=\"Configuration Data Management\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/services/integrated-logistics-support/configuration-data-management/\">Configuration Data Management (CDM)</a></h3>\r\n<p>CDM is a discipline applied to a Configuration Item for its entire lifecycle - defining system configuration with progressive purification. Effective CDM ensures that the defined user requirements of a Configuration Item are met.</p>\r\n<h3><a title=\"ILS Support &amp; Training\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/services/integrated-logistics-support/ils-support-training/\">ILS Support &amp; Training</a></h3>\r\n<p>For decades, ATS has provided our US Navy with the highest level of Integrated Logistics Support providing fleet support, training and assistance during technology insertion.</p>','Integrated Logistics Support','','publish','open','open','','integrated-logistics-support','','','2014-09-17 18:52:59','2014-09-17 18:52:59','',25,'http://dev.atsid.com/?page_id=120',0,'page','',0),(121,3,'2014-07-18 03:48:57','2014-07-18 03:48:57','<h1 id=\"page-title\">Lifecycle Support Solutions</h1>\r\n<div id=\"block-block-20\">\r\n<div data-send=\"false\" data-layout=\"button_count\" data-width=\"89\" data-show-faces=\"false\" data-action=\"recommend\"></div>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.addthis.com/bookmark.php?v=250\"></a>\r\n<div id=\"_atssh\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"block-system-main\"><article id=\"node-basic-page-93\">\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>ATS is focused on innovative and sustainable integrated logistic support and lifecycle support solutions.</strong>\r\n\r\nFor over 30 years, ATS has focused on the development of innovative and sustainable maintenance and lifecycle solutions to product lifecycle system support problems. From the outset, our emphasis has been on finding ways to make the products of the Navys logistics lifecycle support system work for, rather than against, the shipboard maintenance technician.\r\n\r\nMost Operational Availability (Ao) and system sustainability problems experienced by the fleet today can be traced to a failure somewhere in the shore-based lifecycle logistics support system. Lack of onboard repair parts (OBRP) supply support is a particularly acute system sustainability problem, but there are also systemic problems with technical manuals, drawings, configuration and other types of engineering technical data. In many cases these technical data problems are the root cause of OBRP support problems, but they are often perceived as a Supply support problem.\r\n\r\nATS uses our unique product lifecycle maintenance solutions to troubleshoot and correct lifecycle integrated logistics support and sustainability problems. Most of our Maintenance Support Group technicians are former Navy technicians who have extensive experience in the operation and maintenance of the full spectrum of shipboard systems. This maintenance-oriented perspective is fundamental to our view of the integrated logistics support world and our maintenance support analysis processes.\r\n\r\nWe train our maintenance support technicians using our own in-house lifecycle support management training program which we developed from years of hands on experience in all facets of the integrated logistics support system. The end result is an experienced shipboard maintenance technician who is also trained to troubleshoot and repair any element of the Navys integrated logistics support system to make sure the ILS system provides our sailors with the parts, data and tools they need to restore failed systems with minimal delay.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" align=\"left\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">\r\n<h2>Maintenance &amp; Supportability Analysis</h2>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<h2>Configuration Data Management (CDM)</h2>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>ATS has provided preventative and corrective maintenance support solutions to its customers for over 30 years. Analyzing system failures, maintenance actions and technical data that drive logistics support solutions.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://atsid.com/solutions/lifecycle-support-solutions/maintenancesupportability-analysis\">&gt; read more on Maintenance and Supportability</a></td>\r\n<td>CDM is a discipline applied to a Configuration Item for its entire lifecycle - defining system configuration with progressive purification. Effective CDM ensures that the defin