ied Technical Systems?</h2>\r\n<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-127 alignleft\" alt=\"meet-ats-image\" src=\"http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/meet-ats-image-300x216.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"216\" />\r\n\r\nApplied Technical Systems Inc. (ATS) isan expert in cloud-based software solutions, lifecycle support solutions, data analytics, data mining and data visualization.We institute agile software development with user-centered design.<a href=\"http://www.atsid.com/solutions\">Learn more about our solutions </a>\r\n\r\nFounded in1980, ATS has helped government agencies and commercial clients arrive at better decisions through intelligent discovery solutions, total life cycle expertise for the US Navy, and a broad range of systems engineering services. ATS clients include the U.S. Intelligence Community, Department of Commerce, Department of Homeland Security, and the Department of Defense. Headquartered in Silverdale, WA, ATS also has offices in Alexandria and Suffolk, VA.<a href=\"http://www.atsid.com/history\">Explore ATS History </a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[columns number=\"2\"]\r\n\r\n[column]\r\n<h3>Leadership</h3>\r\nLorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Aenean tempor luctus mi non adipiscing. Pellentesque habitant morbi tristique senectus et netus et malesuada fames ac turpis egestas. Integer volutpat enim ac ligula dapibus, ac commodo nibh malesuada.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#\">&gt; read about our leadership</a>\r\n<h3>Patents</h3>\r\nLorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Aenean tempor luctus mi non adipiscing. Pellentesque habitant morbi tristique senectus et netus et malesuada fames ac turpis egestas. Integer volutpat enim ac ligula dapibus, ac commodo nibh malesuada.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#\">&gt; see our patents</a>\r\n\r\n[/column]\r\n\r\n[column]\r\n<h3>Patents</h3>\r\nLorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Aenean tempor luctus mi non adipiscing. Pellentesque habitant morbi tristique senectus et netus et malesuada fames ac turpis egestas. Integer volutpat enim ac ligula dapibus, ac commodo nibh malesuada.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#\">&gt; see our patents</a>\r\n\r\n[/column]\r\n\r\n[/columns]','Meet ATS','','inherit','open','open','','21-revision-v1','','','2014-07-18 03:55:01','2014-07-18 03:55:01','',21,'http://dev.atsid.com/2014/07/18/21-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(129,3,'2014-07-18 20:22:32','2014-07-18 20:22:32','<h3>ATS is Founded</h3>\n<div>\n\nApplied Technical Systems was founded in 1980 by Rick Leenstra upon his retirement from the Navy. Prior to his retirement, Leenstra led an effort to implement the Integrated Logistics Overhaul Program (ILO) fleet wide. The program was formally commissioned as a Navy-wide maintenance improvement effort. Leenstra decided to settle down in Washington with his family upon retirement after 23 years of enlisted and commissioned service. Leenstra was asked by a senior NAVSEA official coordinating the ILO efforts to continue implementing the ILO effort as a contractor. Leensstra agreed and formed ATS as a means to work with the Navy to fully implement the ILO program.\n\n</div>\n<a href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/ADMJackWilliams_1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-280\" src=\"http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/ADMJackWilliams_1-150x142.jpg\" alt=\"ADMJackWilliams_1\" width=\"150\" height=\"142\" /></a>\n<h3>ATS legacy with Admiral J. G. Jack Williams, USN</h3>\n<div>Admiral Jack Williams graduated from the Naval Academy in 1946 and reported to a destroyer as Gun Boss. After completing submarine training he served on USS Pompodon (SS-486) and USS Stickelback (SS-415). He later commanded USS Sterlet (SS-392) and after nuclear power training commanded USS Haddo (SSN-604) and USS Daniel Webster (SSBN-626). After a tour as Director of Training for Naval Reactors, he assumed duties as Force Material Officer (N4) for Commander Submarine Forces, Atlantic. He then took command of Submarine Squadron 16 in Rota, Spain. Upon completion of that tour he was selected for Rear Admiral and subsequently served as Naval Attach to the Turkish Navy. Later he commanded Submarine Group Five in San Diego. Upon promotion to Vice Admiral he served as Deputy Commander, U.S. Pacific Fleet and then as Vice Chief of Naval Operations for Submarine Warfare. In 1981 he was promoted to Admiral and assigned duties as Chief of Naval Material. Admiral Williams retired from the Navy in 1983 and returned to his boyhood home in Illwaco, Washington.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>\n\nIn 1984 he joined ATS as a director and eventually assumed the position of Chairman of the Board, which he held until his unexpected death in 1991. During this period Admiral Williams was instrumental in creating the Naval Undersea Museum in Keyport, served as President of the Northwest Chapter of the Naval Submarine League, and was a key player in helping ATS develop configuration-based lifecycle logistics support solutions for both submarines and surface ships.\n<h3>A heritage in solving complex data problems</h3>\n<div>Several years before XML became a de facto standard, ATS realized the need for a hierarchical, self-describing, data modeling and storage technology. ATS developed the Contiguous Connection Model (CCM) technology to facilitate rapid information retrieval, enhance data navigation and visualization, and promote knowledge discovery. This patented technology (US Patent #s 5,303,367 and 5,555,409), which was revolutionary for its time, automatically correlates hierarchical data, models it, and stores it in expandable name/value pairs. CCM goes much furtherit creates a complete new hierarchical structure for each and every data point, with the data point as the root. These \"inversions\" are permanently stored and can be intuitively browsed using our powerful visualization tools.</div>\n<div>\n\nCCM was the pre-cursor to REGGAE, patented under 8,069,188 which is a core component of the ATS Cloud Analytical Platform. REGGAE is an innovative cellular-like data model to describe and relate complex data structures, perform distributed data analytics and find similar data based on like connections and attributes. The invention in this latest patent provides a means to easily discover behaviors and patterns among seemingly unrelated data. For example, a retail store can easily analyze its customer behaviors to determine which products are more suitable for different demographics. There are numerous applications in healthcare, evidence discovery, threat intelligence, etc.\n\n</div>\n</div>','History','','inherit','open','open','','72-autosave-v1','','','2014-07-18 20:22:32','2014-07-18 20:22:32','',72,'http://dev.atsid.com/2014/07/18/72-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(130,3,'2014-07-18 03:57:18','2014-07-18 03:57:18','<h3>ATS is Founded</h3>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nApplied Technical Systems was founded in 1980 by Rick Leenstra upon his retirement from the Navy. Prior to his retirement, Leenstra led an effort to implement the Integrated Logistics Overhaul Program (ILO) fleet wide. The program was formally commissioned as a Navy-wide maintenance improvement effort. Leenstra decided to settle down in Washington with his family upon retirement after 23 years of enlisted and commissioned service. Leenstra was asked by a senior NAVSEA official coordinating the ILO efforts to continue implementing the ILO effort as a contractor. Leensstra agreed and formed ATS as a means to work with the Navy to fully implement the ILO program.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>ATS legacy with Admiral J. G. Jack Williams, USN</h3>\r\n<div>Admiral Jack Williams graduated from the Naval Academy in 1946 and reported to a destroyer as Gun Boss. After completing submarine training he served on USS Pompodon (SS-486) and USS Stickelback (SS-415). He later commanded USS Sterlet (SS-392) and after nuclear power training commanded USS Haddo (SSN-604) and USS Daniel Webster (SSBN-626). After a tour as Director of Training for Naval Reactors, he assumed duties as Force Material Officer (N4) for Commander Submarine Forces, Atlantic. He then took command of Submarine Squadron 16 in Rota, Spain. Upon completion of that tour he was selected for Rear Admiral and subsequently served as Naval Attach to the Turkish Navy. Later he commanded Submarine Group Five in San Diego. Upon promotion to Vice Admiral he served as Deputy Commander, U.S. Pacific Fleet and then as Vice Chief of Naval Operations for Submarine Warfare. In 1981 he was promoted to Admiral and assigned duties as Chief of Naval Material. Admiral Williams retired from the Navy in 1983 and returned to his boyhood home in Illwaco, Washington.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nIn 1984 he joined ATS as a director and eventually assumed the position of Chairman of the Board, which he held until his unexpected death in 1991. During this period Admiral Williams was instrumental in creating the Naval Undersea Museum in Keyport, served as President of the Northwest Chapter of the Naval Submarine League, and was a key player in helping ATS develop configuration-based lifecycle logistics support solutions for both submarines and surface ships.\r\n<h3>A heritage in solving complex data problems</h3>\r\n<div>Several years before XML became a de facto standard, ATS realized the need for a hierarchical, self-describing, data modeling and storage technology. ATS developed the Contiguous Connection Model (CCM) technology to facilitate rapid information retrieval, enhance data navigation and visualization, and promote knowledge discovery. This patented technology (US Patent #s 5,303,367 and 5,555,409), which was revolutionary for its time, automatically correlates hierarchical data, models it, and stores it in expandable name/value pairs. CCM goes much furtherit creates a complete new hierarchical structure for each and every data point, with the data point as the root. These \"inversions\" are permanently stored and can be intuitively browsed using our powerful visualization tools.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nCCM was the pre-cursor to REGGAE, patented under 8,069,188 which is a core component of the ATS Cloud Analytical Platform. REGGAE is an innovative cellular-like data model to describe and relate complex data structures, perform distributed data analytics and find similar data based on like connections and attributes. The invention in this latest patent provides a means to easily discover behaviors and patterns among seemingly unrelated data. For example, a retail store can easily analyze its customer behaviors to determine which products are more suitable for different demographics. There are numerous applications in healthcare, evidence discovery, threat intelligence, etc.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','History','','inherit','open','open','','72-revision-v1','','','2014-07-18 03:57:18','2014-07-18 03:57:18','',72,'http://dev.atsid.com/2014/07/18/72-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(131,3,'2014-07-18 03:58:01','2014-07-18 03:58:01','<table width=\"100%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"10\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\"><strong>Rick Leenstra, Sr., Chairman and Chief Executive Officer</strong>\r\n\r\nSince founding ATS in 1980 upon his retirement from the US Navy, Rick has applied his extensive experience with configuration-based life cycle maintenance support systems for Naval ships and systems to the development of ATS\' technology and service offerings. Rick is the co-inventor of ATS\' patented CCM technology. As Chairman and CEO, Rick leads the ATS Board of Directors and is responsible for corporate oversight and strategic direction. Rick received his BS from Naval Post Graduate School in 1973 and a MBA from Golden Gate University in 1974.</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"220\">\r\n<div align=\"center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://atsid.com/sites/default/files/Rick_Leenstra-13.png\" /></div></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\"><strong>Bruce MacDonald, President and Chief Operating Officer</strong>\r\n\r\nBruce joined ATS in 2013 as its President and Chief Operating Officer after serving for three years in the Senior Executive Service in the Department of Defense, reporting directly to the Deputy Secretary of Defense. Prior to that, Bruce culminated a 31 year military career serving as the 40th Judge Advocate General of the Navy , becoming the Navys first JAG to attain three-star flag rank. MacDonald graduated from the College of the Holy Cross in 1978 with a Bachelor of Arts degree in English, and entered the Navy in May of that year, serving as an engineering officer on destroyers. He later received his degree of Juris Doctor from California Western School of Law in 1987 and a Master of Laws degree from Harvard Law School in 1992.</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"220\">\r\n<div align=\"center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://atsid.com/sites/default/files/Bruce_MacDonald-13.png\" /></div></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\"><strong>Felicia King, Chief Financial Officer</strong>\r\n\r\nFelicia joined ATS in 1987 and has guided the company through the financial, contractual and human resource challenges of a growing company. She is responsible for finance, accounting, human resources and facilities. She is a Charter Member of the West Sound Chapter of the National Contract Management Association and has been treasurer of the local chapter since 1991. Felicia holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Accounting from Virginia Tech.</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"220\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://atsid.com/sites/default/files/Felicia_King-13.png\" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\"><strong>Ken Smith, Chief Information Officer/Chief Technology Officer</strong>\r\n\r\nKen serves as a science and technology advisor to the management teams within ATS andoversees ATS\'s IT and internal research &amp; development efforts, with a focus on cloud computing, Big Data analytics, information visualization, and user experience design.Prior to joining ATS in 2012, Ken led R&amp;D efforts in text mining, information extraction, and data clustering for projects in support of customers within the Army, Air Force, and Naval Research Laboratory. Ken holds a Ph.D. in Physics from The Pennsylvania State University, where he also taught for three years prior to moving to the Washington, DC area.</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"220\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://atsid.com/sites/default/files/Ken_Smith-13.png\" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\"><strong>Ed Hallda, Vice President, Strategic Development</strong>\r\n\r\nAs both a veteran and contractor, Ed brings more than 20 years of Navy service, technology management and federal business development experience to the fast growing ATS team. Ed is responsible for strategic planning and business development. Prior to joining ATS in 2009, Ed was instrumental in bringing several million dollars of defense contracting to the Kitsap economy. Ed also served as Chief Strategy Officer and Vice President of Engineering &amp; Technology for a public company that formed the largest online mortgage marketplace on the Internet.</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"220\">\r\n<div align=\"center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://atsid.com/sites/default/files/Ed_Hallda-13.png\" /></div></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\"><strong>Carey B. Kolb, Vice President, Systems Engineering</strong>\r\n\r\nCarey joined ATS in 1996 and is responsible for managing and growing the Systems Engineering business, including the sale of professional services and products to the federal government. Carey holds a Bachelor of Business Administration in Finance from the University of Iowa and a Master of Business Administration in Organizational Behavior from the University of Missouri, Kansas City.</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"220\">\r\n<div align=\"center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://atsid.com/sites/default/files/Leadership-CareyKolb.jpg\" width=\"150\" /></div></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\"><strong>Doug West, Vice President, Maintenance Support Group</strong>\r\n\r\nDoug joined ATS in 1988 and has been around the U.S. Navy as a maintenance technician, configuration data manager and readiness analyst for 30 years. He is responsible for all aspects of the Maintenance Support Group business operations. A Disabled Navy veteran, Doug also previously served as an executive at AMSEC LLC. He is one of the founding members of the Service Disabled Veteran Owned Small Business (SDVOSB) Council and serves on the Board of Directors (BOD) as Secretary. Doug holds a Bachelor of Business Administration from Almeda University.</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"220\">\r\n<div align=\"center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://atsid.com/sites/default/files/Leadership-DougWest.jpg\" width=\"150\" /></div></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\"><strong>Jeff Pendry, Director, Systems Engineering</strong>\r\n\r\nJeff is ATSs senior leadership in the D.C. metro area, promoting business development and strategic teaming agreements with industry partners. Jeff joined ATS in 2001 to establish a quality assurance program for ATS and now oversees program management for Systems Engineering. Jeff provides leadership within a variety of IT environments to deliver innovative technology solutions quickly and seamlessly to our customers through an agile framework. As a U.S. Navy veteran and submariner, he adheres to the same principles of honor and integrity and displays this in his commitment to each of his projects and customers. Jeff is a PMI-certified Project Management Professional and a Certified Configuration Manager.</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"220\">\r\n<div align=\"center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://atsid.com/sites/default/files/Leadership-JeffPendry.jpg\" width=\"150\" /></div></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\"><strong>Dennis Wilkelis, Director, Maintenance Support Group</strong>\r\n\r\nDennis originally joined ATS in 1982 to support tasking developing the Standard PMS Material Identification Guide (SPMIG). Dennis assisted ATS in the development and implementation of the Maintenance Support Center (MSC) program which is still in place today. Being a US Navy veteran and gaining familiarization with US Navy systems has allowed him to be an integral part of the ATS team that continues to support the MSC program; C5ISR assessments; and system sustainment of systems in the fleet. Dennis is responsible for product delivery, continuous process improvements, management of project budgets and cost estimates, and over 30 personnel. He takes an active/hands-on management approach. Dennis also has served as Division Manager at AMSEC LLC.</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"220\">\r\n<div align=\"center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://atsid.com/sites/default/files/Dennis_Wilkelis-13.png\" /></div>\r\n&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>','Leadership','','inherit','open','open','','74-revision-v1','','','2014-07-18 03:58:01','2014-07-18 03:58:01','',74,'http://dev.atsid.com/2014/07/18/74-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(132,3,'2014-07-18 20:28:51','2014-07-18 20:28:51','<img class=\"alignright\" src=\"http://www.atsid.com/sites/default/files/styles/large/public/Virtualworld-sm.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"218\" height=\"145\" />\n<table border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"http://patft.uspto.gov/netacgi/nph-Parser?Sect1=PTO2&amp;Sect2=HITOFF&amp;p=1&amp;u=%2Fnetahtml%2FPTO%2Fsearch-bool.html&amp;r=1&amp;f=G&amp;l=50&amp;co1=AND&amp;d=PTXT&amp;s1=5,303,367.PN.&amp;OS=PN/8,069,188&amp;RS=PN/8,069,188\" target=\"_blank\">5,303,367</a></td>\n<td>Computer driven systems and methods for managing data which use two generic data elements and a single ordered file</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"http://patft.uspto.gov/netacgi/nph-Parser?Sect1=PTO2&amp;Sect2=HITOFF&amp;p=1&amp;u=%2Fnetahtml%2FPTO%2Fsearch-bool.html&amp;r=1&amp;f=G&amp;l=50&amp;co1=AND&amp;d=PTXT&amp;s1=5,555,409.PN.&amp;OS=PN/8,069,188&amp;RS=PN/8,069,188\" target=\"_blank\">5,555,409</a></td>\n<td>Data management systems and methods including creation of composite views of data</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"http://patft.uspto.gov/netacgi/nph-Parser?Sect1=PTO2&amp;Sect2=HITOFF&amp;p=1&amp;u=%2Fnetahtml%2FPTO%2Fsearch-bool.html&amp;r=1&amp;f=G&amp;l=50&amp;co1=AND&amp;d=PTXT&amp;s1=8,069,188.PN.&amp;OS=PN/8,069,188&amp;RS=PN/8,069,188\" target=\"_blank\">8,069,188</a></td>\n<td>Database system storing a data structure that includes data nodes connected by context nodes and related method</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3>A heritage in solving complex data problems</h3>\nSeveral years before XML became a de facto standard, ATS realized the need for a hierarchical, self-describing, data modeling and storage technology. ATS developed the Contiguous Connection Model (CCM) technology to facilitate rapid information retrieval, enhance data navigation and visualization, and promote knowledge discovery. This patented technology (US Patent #s 5,303,367 and 5,555,409), which was revolutionary for its time, automatically correlates hierarchical data, models it, and stores it in expandable name/value pairs. CCM goes much furtherit creates a complete new hierarchical structure for each and every data point, with the data point as the root. These \"inversions\" are permanently stored and can be intuitively browsed using our powerful visualization tools.\n\nThe third patent is for a Relational Generating Graph Analysis Engine (REGGAE). REGGAE has an innovative cellular-like data model used to describe and relate complex data structures, perform distributed data analytics and find similar data based on like connections and attributes. The patent was issued as US Patent No. 8,069,188.\n\nWhen asked to describe the value of the patent to ATS, co-author Bryan Tower stated, Since we applied for the patent in early 2008, ATS has implemented this engine in a variety of applications that need to analyze complex data relationships.In the intelligence community, we created an application called Hypergraph that uses the engine to perform distributed data analytics in a secure, private cloud computing environment. It enables analysts to quickly and easily perform multidimensional analysis on millions of text documents. The invention in this patent provides a means to discover behaviors and patterns among seemingly unrelated data. For example, a retail store can easily analyze its customer behaviors to determine which products are more suitable for different demographics. There are numerous applications in healthcare, evidence discovery, threat intelligence, and other areas.\n\nThe CCM technology is the pre-cursor to REGGAE, a core component of the<a href=\"http://atsid.com/solutions/it-solutions/data-analytics\">Arcus Cloud Analytical Platform</a>.\n\n</div>\n&nbsp;','Patents','','inherit','open','open','','78-autosave-v1','','','2014-07-18 20:28:51','2014-07-18 20:28:51','',78,'http://dev.atsid.com/2014/07/18/78-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(133,3,'2014-07-18 04:02:04','2014-07-18 04:02:04','<table border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a href=\"http://patft.uspto.gov/netacgi/nph-Parser?Sect1=PTO2&amp;Sect2=HITOFF&amp;p=1&amp;u=%2Fnetahtml%2FPTO%2Fsearch-bool.html&amp;r=1&amp;f=G&amp;l=50&amp;co1=AND&amp;d=PTXT&amp;s1=5,303,367.PN.&amp;OS=PN/8,069,188&amp;RS=PN/8,069,188\" target=\"_blank\">5,303,367</a></td>\r\n<td>Computer driven systems and methods for managing data which use two generic data elements and a single ordered file</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a href=\"http://patft.uspto.gov/netacgi/nph-Parser?Sect1=PTO2&amp;Sect2=HITOFF&amp;p=1&amp;u=%2Fnetahtml%2FPTO%2Fsearch-bool.html&amp;r=1&amp;f=G&amp;l=50&amp;co1=AND&amp;d=PTXT&amp;s1=5,555,409.PN.&amp;OS=PN/8,069,188&amp;RS=PN/8,069,188\" target=\"_blank\">5,555,409</a></td>\r\n<td>Data management systems and methods including creation of composite views of data</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a href=\"http://patft.uspto.g