\">\r\n<div class=\"field-item even\"><a class=\"ext\" style=\"color: #8a2216;\" href=\"http://www.kitsapsun.com/news/2009/jun/22/business-spotlight-teens-forgo-flipping-burgers/#ixzz1sQSy80mJ\">Teens Forgo Flipping Burgers for More Fruitful Summer Work</a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"field field-name-field-date field-type-datetime field-label-hidden clearfix\" style=\"color: #000000;\">\r\n<div class=\"field-items\">\r\n<div class=\"field-item even\"><span class=\"date-display-single\">Monday, June 22, 2009</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Teens Forgo Flipping Burgers for More Fruitful Summer Work','','inherit','open','open','','246-revision-v1','','','2014-07-18 19:17:14','2014-07-18 19:17:14','',246,'http://dev.atsid.com/2014/07/18/246-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(248,3,'2009-06-22 19:17:18','2009-06-22 19:17:18','<div class=\"field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden clearfix\" style=\"color: #000000;\">\r\n<div class=\"field-items\">\r\n<div class=\"field-item even\">\r\n<h3><strong>Hallda has been instrumental in bringing millions of defense contracting dollars to Kitsap County</strong></h3>\r\n<strong>Silverdale, Wash. - June 22, 2009</strong> Applied Technical Systems (ATS) announced today the appointment of Ed Hallda as Business Development Executive. In this capacity, Mr. Hallda will be responsible for generating new business opportunities in information technology systems and support for government and commercial clients. Mr. Hallda brings over 16 years of Navy service and federal business development experience to the fast growing ATS team.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining ATS, Mr. Hallda served as Business Development Executive for Bremerton, WA-based D4 where he was instrumental in bringing several million dollars of defense contracting to the Kitsap economy. Hallda also served as Chief Strategy Officer and Executive Vice President of Business Development for LION, Inc., where he successfully built business partnerships and strategic alliances to form the largest online business-to-business mortgage marketplace on the Internet.\r\n\r\nEds track record of bringing defense contracting dollars to Kitsap County is truly impressive, said Carey Kolb, Vice President of Applied Technical Systems. He brings to ATS a diverse background in both technology and federal business development, plus an extensive network of Department of Defense contacts. I am thrilled to welcome him to the ATS team.\r\n\r\nMr. Halldas technology background includes six years in the Navy as an Electronics Technician and six years supporting the Navy as a contracted Computer Specialist with Vitro, Inc. where he designed custom database applications with a concentration on project and maintenance transparency and analysis. Mr. Hallda then founded a local Internet Service Provider business in Kitsap County and acted as a private consultant to many Washington-based companies including LION, Inc where he led a team of engineers that developed the first mortgage application on the Internet to successfully transmit automated underwriting data to Fannie Mae for mortgage loan approval.\r\n\r\nI have been impressed with the depth and breadth of services ATS is able to provide to government and commercial clients, said Mr. Hallda. In the information technology sector alone, ATS strong past performance qualifications in systems integration, software development, IT help desk and business process automation position the company for rapid growth.\r\n\r\n<strong>About Applied Technical Systems</strong>\r\n\r\nWith headquarters in Silverdale, WA, and offices in Washington, DC and Suffolk, VA, Applied Technical Systems (ATS) provides information exploitation and naval logistics services and technologies to customers within the U.S. Intelligence Community, Department of Homeland Security, Department of Defense and Washington State Government. ATS also provides mission-critical IT support services to both government and commercial customers, and has developed REGGAE, a patent pending, disruptive database technology that holds the potential to fundamentally change the way the nations leading intelligence and law enforcement agencies approach data. For more information about ATS, visit<a style=\"color: #8a2216;\" href=\"http://www.atsid.com/\">http://www.atsid.com</a>or call 360.698.7100.\r\n\r\n###\r\n\r\n<strong>For more information, contact:</strong>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"field field-name-field-contact-name field-type-text field-label-hidden clearfix\" style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #000000;\">\r\n<div class=\"field-items\">\r\n<div class=\"field-item even\">Eric Portney</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"field field-name-field-contact-phone field-type-text field-label-hidden clearfix\" style=\"color: #000000;\">\r\n<div class=\"field-items\">\r\n<div class=\"field-item even\">360.698.7100, x228</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"field field-name-field-contact-email field-type-email field-label-hidden clearfix\" style=\"color: #000000;\">\r\n<div class=\"field-items\">\r\n<div class=\"field-item even\"><a class=\"mailto\" style=\"color: #8a2216;\" href=\"mailto:eric.portney@atsid.com\">eric.portney@atsid.com</a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Federal Business Development Executive Ed Hallda Joins Applied Technical Systems','','publish','open','open','','federal-business-development-executive-ed-hallda-joins-applied-technical-systems','','','2014-07-18 19:18:46','2014-07-18 19:18:46','',0,'http://dev.atsid.com/?p=248',0,'post','',0),(249,3,'2014-07-18 19:17:59','2014-07-18 19:17:59','','lss_index','Keeping ships ready since 1980','inherit','open','open','','lss_index','','','2014-07-18 19:17:59','2014-07-18 19:17:59','',120,'http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/lss_index.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(250,3,'2014-07-18 19:18:13','2014-07-18 19:18:13','[caption id=\"attachment_249\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"213\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-249\" src=\"http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/lss_index.jpg\" alt=\"Keeping ships ready since 1980\" width=\"213\" height=\"142\" /> Keeping ships ready since 1980[/caption]\r\n<h2>ATS is focused on innovative and sustainable integrated logistic support and lifecycle support solutions.</h2>\r\nFor over 30 years, ATS has focused on the development of innovative and sustainable maintenance and lifecycle solutions to product lifecycle system support problems. From the outset, our emphasis has been on finding ways to make the products of the Navys logistics lifecycle support system work for, rather than against, the shipboard maintenance technician.\r\n\r\nMost Operational Availability (Ao) and system sustainability problems experienced by the fleet today can be traced to a failure somewhere in the shore-based lifecycle logistics support system. Lack of onboard repair parts (OBRP) supply support is a particularly acute system sustainability problem, but there are also systemic problems with technical manuals, drawings, configuration and other types of engineering technical data. In many cases these technical data problems are the root cause of OBRP support problems, but they are often perceived as a Supply support problem.\r\n\r\nATS uses our unique product lifecycle maintenance solutions to troubleshoot and correct lifecycle integrated logistics support and sustainability problems. Most of our Maintenance Support Group technicians are former Navy technicians who have extensive experience in the operation and maintenance of the full spectrum of shipboard systems. This maintenance-oriented perspective is fundamental to our view of the integrated logistics support world and our maintenance support analysis processes.\r\n\r\nWe train our maintenance support technicians using our own in-house lifecycle support management training program which we developed from years of hands on experience in all facets of the integrated logistics support system. The end result is an experienced shipboard maintenance technician who is also trained to troubleshoot and repair any element of the Navys integrated logistics support system to make sure the ILS system provides our sailors with the parts, data and tools they need to restore failed systems with minimal delay.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" align=\"left\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">\r\n<h2>Maintenance &amp; Supportability Analysis</h2>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<h2>Configuration Data Management (CDM)</h2>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>ATS has provided preventative and corrective maintenance support solutions to its customers for over 30 years. Analyzing system failures, maintenance actions and technical data that drive logistics support solutions.<a href=\"http://atsid.com/solutions/lifecycle-support-solutions/maintenancesupportability-analysis\">&gt; read more on Maintenance and Supportability</a></td>\r\n<td>CDM is a discipline applied to a Configuration Item for its entire lifecycle - defining system configuration with progressive purification. Effective CDM ensures that the defined user requirements of a Configuration Item are met.<a href=\"http://atsid.com/solutions/lifecycle-support-solutions/configuration-data-management\">&gt; read more on Configuration Data Management</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h2>Product Lifecycle Management (PLM)</h2>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<h2>ILS Support &amp; Training</h2>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>We can deliver a single, authoritative source for product and lifecycle data. Let ATS help you harness the power of Product Lifecycle Management (PLM) processes and systems that can transform your current processes.<a href=\"http://atsid.com/solutions/lifecycle-support-solutions/product-lifecycle-management\">&gt; read more on Product Lifecycle Management</a></td>\r\n<td>For over 30 years, ATS has provided our US Navy with the highest level of Integrated Logistics Support providing fleet support, training and assistance during technology insertion.<a href=\"http://atsid.com/solutions/lifecycle-support-solutions/ils-support-training\">&gt; read more on Integrated Logistics Support</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\n<br />','Lifecycle Support Solutions','','inherit','open','open','','120-revision-v1','','','2014-07-18 19:18:13','2014-07-18 19:18:13','',120,'http://dev.atsid.com/2014/07/18/120-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(251,3,'2014-07-18 19:18:46','2014-07-18 19:18:46','<div class=\"field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden clearfix\" style=\"color: #000000;\">\r\n<div class=\"field-items\">\r\n<div class=\"field-item even\">\r\n<h3><strong>Hallda has been instrumental in bringing millions of defense contracting dollars to Kitsap County</strong></h3>\r\n<strong>Silverdale, Wash. - June 22, 2009</strong> Applied Technical Systems (ATS) announced today the appointment of Ed Hallda as Business Development Executive. In this capacity, Mr. Hallda will be responsible for generating new business opportunities in information technology systems and support for government and commercial clients. Mr. Hallda brings over 16 years of Navy service and federal business development experience to the fast growing ATS team.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining ATS, Mr. Hallda served as Business Development Executive for Bremerton, WA-based D4 where he was instrumental in bringing several million dollars of defense contracting to the Kitsap economy. Hallda also served as Chief Strategy Officer and Executive Vice President of Business Development for LION, Inc., where he successfully built business partnerships and strategic alliances to form the largest online business-to-business mortgage marketplace on the Internet.\r\n\r\nEds track record of bringing defense contracting dollars to Kitsap County is truly impressive, said Carey Kolb, Vice President of Applied Technical Systems. He brings to ATS a diverse background in both technology and f