s</li>\r\n	<li>Workflow mapping</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>User-centered, iterative design</li>\r\n	<li>Rapid software prototyping</li>\r\n	<li>UI and quality testing</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><b>Deployment &amp; Training</b></td>\r\n<td><b>Optimization &amp; Maintenance</b></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Phased software rollout</li>\r\n	<li>Onsite and online training</li>\r\n	<li>Documentation authoring</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Feedback gathering</li>\r\n	<li>System enhancements</li>\r\n	<li>Maintenance &amp; upgrades</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/meet-ats/contact-us/\">Contact ATS today</a>to discuss your next software development project.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"></p>','Software Development','','inherit','open','open','','171-revision-v1','','','2014-07-18 20:09:30','2014-07-18 20:09:30','',171,'http://dev.atsid.com/2014/07/18/171-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(280,3,'2014-07-18 20:21:42','2014-07-18 20:21:42','ADM Jack Williams, then Chief of Naval Material teaching COSAL','ADMJackWilliams_1','','inherit','open','open','','admjackwilliams_1','','','2014-07-18 20:21:42','2014-07-18 20:21:42','',72,'http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/ADMJackWilliams_1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(281,3,'2014-07-18 20:22:55','2014-07-18 20:22:55','<h3>ATS is Founded</h3>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nApplied Technical Systems was founded in 1980 by Rick Leenstra upon his retirement from the Navy. Prior to his retirement, Leenstra led an effort to implement the Integrated Logistics Overhaul Program (ILO) fleet wide. The program was formally commissioned as a Navy-wide maintenance improvement effort. Leenstra decided to settle down in Washington with his family upon retirement after 23 years of enlisted and commissioned service. Leenstra was asked by a senior NAVSEA official coordinating the ILO efforts to continue implementing the ILO effort as a contractor. Leensstra agreed and formed ATS as a means to work with the Navy to fully implement the ILO program.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_280\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"150\"]<a href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/ADMJackWilliams_1.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-280 size-thumbnail\" src=\"http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/ADMJackWilliams_1-150x142.jpg\" alt=\"ADMJackWilliams_1\" width=\"150\" height=\"142\" /></a> ADM Jack Williams, then Chief of Naval Material teaching COSAL[/caption]\r\n<h3>ATS legacy with Admiral J. G. Jack Williams, USN</h3>\r\n<div>Admiral Jack Williams graduated from the Naval Academy in 1946 and reported to a destroyer as Gun Boss. After completing submarine training he served on USS Pompodon (SS-486) and USS Stickelback (SS-415). He later commanded USS Sterlet (SS-392) and after nuclear power training commanded USS Haddo (SSN-604) and USS Daniel Webster (SSBN-626). After a tour as Director of Training for Naval Reactors, he assumed duties as Force Material Officer (N4) for Commander Submarine Forces, Atlantic. He then took command of Submarine Squadron 16 in Rota, Spain. Upon completion of that tour he was selected for Rear Admiral and subsequently served as Naval Attach to the Turkish Navy. Later he commanded Submarine Group Five in San Diego. Upon promotion to Vice Admiral he served as Deputy Commander, U.S. Pacific Fleet and then as Vice Chief of Naval Operations for Submarine Warfare. In 1981 he was promoted to Admiral and assigned duties as Chief of Naval Material. Admiral Williams retired from the Navy in 1983 and returned to his boyhood home in Illwaco, Washington.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nIn 1984 he joined ATS as a director and eventually assumed the position of Chairman of the Board, which he held until his unexpected death in 1991. During this period Admiral Williams was instrumental in creating the Naval Undersea Museum in Keyport, served as President of the Northwest Chapter of the Naval Submarine League, and was a key player in helping ATS develop configuration-based lifecycle logistics support solutions for both submarines and surface ships.\r\n<h3>A heritage in solving complex data problems</h3>\r\n<div>Several years before XML became a de facto standard, ATS realized the need for a hierarchical, self-describing, data modeling and storage technology. ATS developed the Contiguous Connection Model (CCM) technology to facilitate rapid information retrieval, enhance data navigation and visualization, and promote knowledge discovery. This patented technology (US Patent #s 5,303,367 and 5,555,409), which was revolutionary for its time, automatically correlates hierarchical data, models it, and stores it in expandable name/value pairs. CCM goes much furtherit creates a complete new hierarchical structure for each and every data point, with the data point as the root. These \"inversions\" are permanently stored and can be intuitively browsed using our powerful visualization tools.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nCCM was the pre-cursor to REGGAE, patented under 8,069,188 which is a core component of the ATS Cloud Analytical Platform. REGGAE is an innovative cellular-like data model to describe and relate complex data structures, perform distributed data analytics and find similar data based on like connections and attributes. The invention in this latest patent provides a means to easily discover behaviors and patterns among seemingly unrelated data. For example, a retail store can easily analyze its customer behaviors to determine which products are more suitable for different demographics. There are numerous applications in healthcare, evidence discovery, threat intelligence, etc.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','History','','inherit','open','open','','72-revision-v1','','','2014-07-18 20:22:55','2014-07-18 20:22:55','',72,'http://dev.atsid.com/2014/07/18/72-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(282,3,'2014-07-18 20:28:58','2014-07-18 20:28:58','<img class=\"alignright\" src=\"http://www.atsid.com/sites/default/files/styles/large/public/Virtualworld-sm.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"218\" height=\"145\" />\r\n<table border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a href=\"http://patft.uspto.gov/netacgi/nph-Parser?Sect1=PTO2&amp;Sect2=HITOFF&amp;p=1&amp;u=%2Fnetahtml%2FPTO%2Fsearch-bool.html&amp;r=1&amp;f=G&amp;l=50&amp;co1=AND&amp;d=PTXT&amp;s1=5,303,367.PN.&amp;OS=PN/8,069,188&amp;RS=PN/8,069,188\" target=\"_blank\">5,303,367</a></td>\r\n<td>Computer driven systems and methods for managing data which use two generic data elements and a single ordered file</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a href=\"http://patft.uspto.gov/netacgi/nph-Parser?Sect1=PTO2&amp;Sect2=HITOFF&amp;p=1&amp;u=%2Fnetahtml%2FPTO%2Fsearch-bool.html&amp;r=1&amp;f=G&amp;l=50&amp;co1=AND&amp;d=PTXT&amp;s1=5,555,409.PN.&amp;OS=PN/8,069,188&amp;RS=PN/8,069,188\" target=\"_blank\">5,555,409</a></td>\r\n<td>Data management systems and methods including creation of composite views of data</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a href=\"http://patft.uspto.gov/netacgi/nph-Parser?Sect1=PTO2&amp;Sect2=HITOFF&amp;p=1&amp;u=%2Fnetahtml%2FPTO%2Fsearch-bool.html&amp;r=1&amp;f=G&amp;l=50&amp;co1=AND&amp;d=PTXT&amp;s1=8,069,188.PN.&amp;OS=PN/8,069,188&amp;RS=PN/8,069,188\" target=\"_blank\">8,069,188</a></td>\r\n<td>Database system storing a data structure that includes data nodes connected by context nodes and related method</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h3>A heritage in solving complex data problems</h3>\r\nSeveral years before XML became a de facto standard, ATS realized the need for a hierarchical, self-describing, data modeling and storage technology. ATS developed the Contiguous Connection Model (CCM) technology to facilitate rapid information retrieval, enhance data navigation and visualization, and promote knowledge discovery. This patented technology (US Patent #s 5,303,367 and 5,555,409), which was revolutionary for its time, automatically correlates hierarchical data, models it, and stores it in expandable name/value pairs. CCM goes much furtherit creates a complete new hierarchical structure for each and every data point, with the data point as the root. These \"inversions\" are permanently stored and can be intuitively browsed using our powerful visualization tools.\r\n\r\nThe third patent is for a Relational Generating Graph Analysis Engine (REGGAE). REGGAE has an innovative cellular-like data model used to describe and relate complex data structures, perform distributed data analytics and find similar data based on like connections and attributes. The patent was issued as US Patent No. 8,069,188.\r\n\r\nWhen asked to describe the value of the patent to ATS, co-author Bryan Tower stated, Since we applied for the patent in early 2008, ATS has implemented this engine in a variety of applications that need to analyze complex data relationships.In the intelligence community, we created an application called Hypergraph that uses the engine to perform distributed data analytics in a secure, private cloud computing environment. It enables analysts to quickly and easily perform multidimensional analysis on millions of text documents. The invention in this patent provides a means to discover behaviors and patterns among seemingly unrelated data. For example, a retail store can easily analyze its customer behaviors to determine which products are more suitable for different demographics. There are numerous applications in healthcare, evidence discovery, threat intelligence, and other areas.\r\n\r\nThe CCM technology is the pre-cursor to REGGAE, a core component of the<a href=\"http://atsid.com/solutions/it-solutions/data-analytics\">Arcus Cloud Analytical Platform</a>.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;','Patents','','inherit','open','open','','78-revision-v1','','','2014-07-18 20:28:58','2014-07-18 20:28:58','',78,'http://dev.atsid.com/2014/07/18/78-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(285,3,'2014-07-18 21:03:12','2014-07-18 21:03:12','','msc1','Maintenance Support Center Data Analysis','inherit','open','open','','msc1','','','2014-07-18 21:03:12','2014-07-18 21:03:12','',260,'http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/msc1.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(287,3,'2014-07-18 21:08:49','2014-07-18 21:08:49','[caption id=\"attachment_288\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"213\"]<img class=\"wp-image-288 size-full\" src=\"http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/data-management.jpg\" alt=\"Defining, purifying and maintaining critical system data.\" width=\"213\" height=\"142\" /> Defining, purifying and maintaining critical system data.[/caption]\r\n<h3>Defining system configuration managementto the maintenance level and maintaining it with progressive purification</h3>\r\n<div style=\"color: #000000;\">Configuration Data Management (CDM) is a discipline applied to a Configuration Item for its entire life cycle. Effective CDM ensures that the defined user requirements of a Configuration Item are met. The four functions of Configuration Data Management are:</div>\r\n<ul style=\"color: #000000;\">\r\n	<li>Configuration Identification (CI) - Identifies the item, and establishes and maintains a basis for control and status accounting for an item or productthroughout its life cycle.</li>\r\n	<li>Configuration Control (CC) - Controls the proposal, justification, evaluation, and coordination of all changes to a Configuration Item (e.g., ECPs, RFDs, RFWs, ERRs, etc.) and its documentation for clear configuration management of the item.</li>\r\n	<li>Configuration Status Accounting (CSA) - Records and reports information required to manage the documentation; the status of the proposed changes, deviations, and waivers; the implementation status of approved changes; and the management of Configuration Items in the operational inventory. CSA ensures effective logistic support.</li>\r\n	<li>Configuration Audit (CA) - Consists of a Functional (FCA) configuration audit and Physical (PCA) configuration audit conducted by the government prior to accepting a Configuration Item and establishing a product baseline. The CA verifies that the Configuration Item complies with its corresponding configuration information.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">ATS is recognized as Configuration Data Management experts. The US Navy relies on ATS to perform Configuration Data Management for many of its complex shipboard systems and regularly performs Configuration Management Audits.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">With its data management software, Configuration Data Analysts and Configuration Data Specialists, ATS can help you implement and/or support a sustainable Configuration Data Management strategy.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/meet-ats/contact-us/\">Contact ATS today</a>to learn more about Configuration Data Management and our data managementsolutions to meet your needs and budget.</p>','Configuration Data Management','','publish','open','open','','configuration-data-management','','','2014-07-18 21:09:20','2014-07-18 21:09:20','',120,'http://dev.atsid.com/?page_id=287',0,'page','',0),(288,3,'2014-07-18 21:06:34','2014-07-18 21:06:34','','data-management','Defining, purifying and maintaining critical system data.','inherit','open','open','','data-management','','','2014-07-18 21:06:34','2014-07-18 21:06:34','',287,'http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/data-management.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(289,3,'2014-07-18 21:08:49','2014-07-18 21:08:49','[caption id=\"attachment_288\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"213\"]<img class=\"wp-image-288 size-full\" src=\"http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/data-management.jpg\" alt=\"Defining, purifying and maintaining critical system data.\" width=\"213\" height=\"142\" /> Defining, purifying and maintaining critical system data.[/caption]\r\n<h3>Defining system configuration managementto the maintenance level and maintaining it with progressive purification</h3>\r\n<div style=\"color: #000000;\">Configuration Data Management (CDM) is a discipline applied to a Configuration Item for its entire life cycle. Effective CDM ensures that the defined user requirements of a Configuration Item are met. The four functions of Configuration Data Management are:</div>\r\n<ul style=\"color: #000000;\">\r\n	<li>Configuration Identification (CI) - Identifies the item, and establishes and maintains a basis for control and status accounting for an item or productthroughout its life cycle.</li>\r\n	<li>Configuration Control (CC) - Controls the proposal, justification, evaluation, and coordination of all changes to a Configuration Item (e.g., ECPs, RFDs, RFWs, ERRs, etc.) and its documentation for clear configuration management of the item.</li>\r\n	<li>Configuration Status Accounting (CSA) - Records and reports information required to manage the documentation; the status of the proposed changes, deviations, and waivers; the implementation status of approved changes; and the management of Configuration Items in the operational inventory. CSA ensures effective logistic support.</li>\r\n	<li>Configuration Audit (CA) - Consists of a Functional (FCA) configuration audit and Physical (PCA) configuration audit conducted by the government prior to accepting a Configuration Item and establishing a product baseline. The CA verifies that the Configuration Item complies with its corresponding configuration information.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">ATS is recognized as Configuration Data Management experts. The US Navy relies on ATS to perform Configuration Data Management for many of its complex shipboard systems and regularly performs Configuration Management Audits.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">With its data management software, Configuration Data Analysts and Configuration Data Specialists, ATS can help you implement and/or support a sustainable Configuration Data Management strategy.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/meet-ats/contact-us/\">Contact ATS today</a>to learn more about Configuration Data Management and our data managementsolutions to meet your needs and budget.</p>','Configuration Data Management','','inherit','open','open','','287-revision-v1','','','2014-07-18 21:08:49','2014-07-18 21:08:49','',287,'http://dev.atsid.com/2014/07/18/287-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(291,3,'2014-07-18 21:13:34','2014-07-18 21:13:34','','product-lifecycle-managemen','Managing data from design to disposal','inherit','open','open','','product-lifecycle-managemen','','','2014-07-18 21:13:34','2014-07-18 21:13:34','',120,'http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/product-lifecycle-managemen.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(293,3,'2014-07-18 21:23:28','2014-07-18 21:23:28','<aside class=\"alignright\">\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_294\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"213\"]<img class=\"wp-image-294 size-full\" src=\"http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/msc3.png\" alt=\"msc3\" width=\"213\" height=\"142\" /> ATS and the US Navy in the MSC[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_295\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"213\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-295\" src=\"http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/underway_0.jpg\" alt=\"Keeping our fleet afloat and ready since 1980\" width=\"213\" height=\"142\" /> Keeping our fleet afloat and ready since 1980[/caption]\r\n\r\n</aside>\r\n<h3>Arming the maintenance and support community with the latest logistics support knowledge and logistics system processes</h3>\r\nFor over 30 years, ATS has provided our US Navy with the highest level of Integrated Logistics Support(ILS) to ensure our ships are ready to set sea. ATS presently provides the followinglogistics supportservices to all COMNAVAIRPAC (CNAP) / COMNAVAIRLANT (CNAL) aircraft carriers and other battle group vessels:\r\n<ul style=\"color: #000000;\">\r\n	<li>Maintenance Support Center (MSC)</li>\r\n	<li>Integrated Logistic Support (ILS)</li>\r\n	<li>Acquisition and Life Cycle Management Services for Command, Control, Communications, Computers, Combat Systems, Intelligence, Surveillance, and Reconnaissance (C5ISR), Hull, Mechanical and Electrical (HM&amp;E) and shipboard Aviation Systems.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">ATS is comprised of maintenance technicians and data integration experts. ATS brings a unique approach to any systems engineering effort by ensuring a key focus area is product or systemlifecycle supportability and maintainability within the existing infrastructure of the business or organization. ATS hires maintenance technicians that have operated and maintained systems and equipment. We then train them in our logistic supportprocedures that were the basis of the Integrated Shipboard Maintenance Support (ISMS) training developed by ATS over 25 years ago and still maintained today. By hiring personnel already familiar with systems and equipment, we have personnel that can easily communicate with any other technician we come in contact with about systems  with an advantage  our personnel also understand the ins and outs of logistics support systems and logistics solutions.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>ATS Integrated Logistic Support services include but are not limited to the following:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"color: #000000;\">\r\n	<li>System Configuration Identification &amp; Validation - System Diagrammatics - Configuration Item / Technical Information (CI-TI) Database Development - System Failure Analysis - Preventative Maintenance / Supportability Analysis - Ship Change Document (SCD)/Non-SCD Identification and Tracking</li>\r\n	<li>Integrated Logistic Support Troubleshooting and Repair</li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"ILS Training Services\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/our-solutions/lifecycle-support-solutions/ils-support-training/ils-training-services/\">Technical &amp; Logistics Training</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"ILS Systems