aring contribution at the end of the fiscal year, which will be divided between employee-elected accounts based on your compensation for the year. The employee must be employed on the last day of the fiscal year (9/30) to be eligible. Vesting starts after two years and an employee is 100% vested after five years.</p>\n<h3>Flexible Schedule</h3>\n<p>We realize not all our employees enjoy getting up before the birds and that not everyone prefers to work into the evening hours. As long as your preferred schedule meets your supervisors approval and your projects needs you can choose your own schedule.</p>\n<h2>Leave/Holidays</h2>\n<h3>Paid Time Off (PTO)</h3>\n<p>Most new permanent, full-time employees earn 96 hours (12 days) of Paid Time Off throughout the year, which will accrue during each pay period. If you stay with the company long enough (we think youll like us), you could earn up to 296 hours (37 days) of PTO a year!<br /> ?</p>\n<h3>Holidays</h3>\n<p>Our employees enjoy the flexibility of 10 floating holidays (80 hours), which can be used at any time during the year. New employees will receive prorated holiday pay based on when in the fiscal year they join us.<br /> ?</p>\n<h3>Bereavement</h3>\n<p>In the event of the loss of an immediate family member, we will grant permanent employees up to five working days of bereavement leave without the loss of pay.</p>\n<h3>Disability</h3>\n<h3><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.4; color: #333333;\">Permanent employees normally scheduled to work at least 20 hours per week are eligible for disability leave accrual (paid for by ATS). Disability leave is accrued at the rate of one day per month (1/2 day for part-time employees). Up to 6 weeks of disability leave may be granted as maternity leave. Up to 6 additional weeks of personal leave and/or leave without pay may be taken if desired.</span></h3>\n<h2><img src=\"http://www.guardianlife.com/glifepp/fragments/glic_assets_frag/images/guardian-logo.gif\" alt=\"\" /></h2>\n<h2>Life Insurance</h2>\n<p>ATS offers company-paid term life insurance for each employee at no cost to the employee in the amount of three times the basic annual salary to a maximum of $500,000. In the case of accidental death, the amount is six times the basic annual salary to a maximum of $1,000,000.<br /> We also have additional supplemental life insurance available for employees, their spouses and their children at the employees expense.<br /> In addition, we also offer group plans (premiums paid through payroll deduction) for the following supplemental insurance packages:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Personal Accident Expense</li>\n<li>Personal Cancer Protector</li>\n<li>Hospital Intensive Care Plan</li>\n<li>Personal Recovery Plus</li>\n</ul>\n<p>?</p>\n<h3>Tuition Assistance</h3>\n<p>?<br /> We love to expand our knowledge, and we want our employees to as well. We offer tuition assistance to our employees when they are furthering their education in a field directly related to their work here at ATS. Employees must complete the course with a 3.0 or better. In return, the employee will be required to work one full year beyond the completion date of the last class taken.<br /> ?</p>\n<h3>Personal Computer Loan Program</h3>\n<p>ATS will fund the purchase of PCs for employee home use through an interest-free loan up to $3,000. The employee will repay the loan within 12 months through a payroll deduction.<br /> ?</p>\n<h3>Friendly, Fun Atmosphere</h3>\n<p>While the size of offices vary from location to location, we all have one thing in common: we enjoy working together.Youll often see employees ordering takeout and spending their lunchtime together. People will bring in plants and goodies from their garden and baked goods from home to share with everyone. During December, some employees may put together a meal rotation so breakfast, lunch and a later meal are always available to enjoy. We even have a company soccer team and an \"Adopt-a-Road\" volunteer team. Thats how much we like each other we are willing to spend time away from work with each other!<br /> ?</p>\n<h3>Relocation Assistance:</h3>\n<p>ATS may provide relocation assistance for certain positions. (Ask your interviewer whether the position is eligible for relocation assistance.) Note: relocation benefits are not available for hourly positions.</p>','Benefits','','inherit','open','open','','328-autosave-v1','','','2014-08-21 21:44:15','2014-08-21 21:44:15','',328,'http://dev.atsid.com/2014/07/18/328-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(333,3,'2014-07-18 22:08:28','2014-07-18 22:08:28','<aside class=\"alignright\">\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_330\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"213\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-330\" src=\"http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/EOQ.jpg\" alt=\"Employee of the Quarter earns you a shopping spree\" width=\"213\" height=\"142\" /> Employee of the Quarter earns you a shopping spree[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_331\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"213\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-331\" src=\"http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/Nathan-iPad.jpg\" alt=\"Qualify for a free iPad for new hire referrals\" width=\"213\" height=\"142\" /> Qualify for a free iPad for new hire referrals[/caption]\r\n</aside>\r\n\r\nThere are many things to consider when deciding on your next employer. At ATS we offer employees the chance to work with great people, on exciting projects, with a ton of opportunity for growth.\r\nBut we also recognize that ATSers have a life outside of work and need a break every once in a while. That\'s why we provide a full range of benefits for you and your eligible family members. While the benefits may vary slightly from location to location, these are the basics for full-time, U.S. employees:\r\n<img src=\"https://www.premera.com/stellent/groups/public/documents/xcpproject/img_logo.gif\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<strong>Medical, Dental and Vision</strong>\r\nOur employees are ou