dy>\r\n</table>\r\n<h3>Our Culture</h3>\r\n<p>Every ATS employee brings value to our team of athletes. Learn more about what drives us as a company and what our people are saying!</p>\r\n<p>&gt; <a title=\"Our Culture\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/careers/our-culture/\">ATS culture</a>  &gt; <a title=\"Employee Testimonials\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/careers/employee-testimonials/\">employee testimonials</a></p>\r\n<h3>Our Benefits</h3>\r\n<p>ATS offers a full range of benefits for you and your eligible family members.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Medical, Dental and Vision</li>\r\n<li>401K Matching</li>\r\n<li>Profit Sharing</li>\r\n<li>Paid Time Off</li>\r\n<li>Life Insurance</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Ask about our additional fringe benefits during your interview</p>\r\n<p>&gt;<a title=\"Benefits\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/careers/benefits/\"> see all ATS benefits</a></p>\r\n<h2>Current Opportunities</h2>\r\n<p>ATS is always looking for top talent in the following roles:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Senior Software Engineers &amp; Software Architects</li>\r\n<li>UI/UX Designers</li>\r\n<li>Project Managers &amp; Project Coordinators</li>\r\n<li>Senior Configuration Managers</li>\r\n<li>Integrated Logistics Specialists</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&gt; <a title=\"Current Openings\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/careers/current-openings/\">to see a complete list of openings, click here</a></p>','Careers','','inherit','open','open','','29-revision-v1','','','2014-08-21 21:54:54','2014-08-21 21:54:54','',29,'http://dev.atsid.com/2014/08/21/29-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(564,3,'2014-08-21 21:57:24','2014-08-21 21:57:24','<h2>Raising Crew Performance</h2>\r\n<div style=\"color: #000000;\">Applied Technical Systems Crew Atlas platform provides tools and metrics to help plants monitor, measure, manage, and improve crew performance.</div>\r\n<div style=\"color: #000000;\"></div>\r\n<div style=\"color: #000000;\">\r\n<h3>Cost Savings</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Plants can substantially reduce costs associated with Initial License and Requalification Training by using ATS Crew Atlas software to identify and target weak areas, raise performance, and reduce/eliminate exam failures.</li>\r\n<li>To comply with NRC Initial License Requirements, plants must initially train operators for a license (10 C.F.R. 50.120).</li>\r\n<li>It costs a plant approximately $500K to initially train and license each control room operator.</li>\r\n<li>At one plant, two (2) operators failed their Initial License Exams, a lost investment of $1M.</li>\r\n<li>Licensed Operators must also re-qualify for their licenses annually, resulting in additional monetary and administrative costs (e.g. increased training and instructor man-hours).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Best Practice Technology</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>ATS Crew Atlas platform was recognized as an industry best practice during site inspections.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Public Protection</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>ATS Crew Atlas platform allows a station to specifically target and improve operator performance to eliminate or significantly reduce the severity of potential disasters.</li>\r\n<li>Crew Atlas provides ongoing, mobile, and real time monitoring of performance and potential gaps to excellence.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h2>Key Features</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>Crew Atlas is a Software as a Service (SaaS) subscription that includes all software updates and maintenance.</div>\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Fully Automated Crew Critique</strong><strong>Process</strong>- Lowers instructor manhoursby leveraging technology to provide detailed metrics and graded reports <strong>Single, Central Performance Repository</strong>- Eliminates multiple,redundant, and outdated network files and stove-piped databases by tracking all aspects of individual and crew performance in one, easily accessible location <strong>Dashboards</strong>- Provides managers with meaningful insight into individual, crew, and fleet performance levels through interactive and dynamic reporting <strong>Risk Mitigation</strong>- Allows managers to generate track and trend action plans to correct specific performance deficiencies <strong>Mobile</strong>- Accessible from any device (e.g. desktop, laptop, tablet, smartphone)</td>\r\n<td><strong>For more information:</strong>\r\n<p>email:<br /><a class=\"mailto\" style=\"color: #8a2216;\" href=\"mailto:crew-atlas@atsid.com\">crew-atlas@atsid.com</a></p>\r\n<p>phone: <br />253.514.2432</p>\r\n<p>View:<br /><a style=\"color: #8a2216;\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/ATS-CrewAtlas-FS.pdf\">Crew Atlas Fact Sheet</a></p>\r\n<p>View:<br /><a style=\"color: #8a2216;\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/ATS-CrewQuiz-FS.pdf\">Crew Quiz Fact Sheet</a></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><b>Noted as Industry Training Best Practice by several site inspectors</b></td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><a style=\"color: #8a2216;\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/meet-ats/contact-us/?interest=crew-atlas\"><img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"http://atsid.com/sites/default/files/request-demo2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"45\" /></a></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Crew Atlas','','inherit','open','open','','200-revision-v1','','','2014-08-21 21:57:24','2014-08-21 21:57:24','',200,'http://dev.atsid.com/2014/08/21/200-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(565,3,'2014-08-21 21:58:50','2014-08-21 21:58:50','[caption id=\"attachment_249\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"213\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-249\" src=\"http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/lss_index.jpg\" alt=\"Keeping ships ready since 1980\" width=\"213\" height=\"142\" /> Keeping ships ready since 1980[/caption]\r\n<h2>ATS is focused on innovative and sustainable integrated logistic support and lifecycle support solutions.</h2>\r\n<p>For over 30 years, ATS has focused on the development of innovative and sustainable maintenance and lifecycle solutions to product lifecycle system support problems. From the outset, our emphasis has been on finding ways to make the products of the Navys logistics lifecycle support system work for, rather than against, the shipboard maintenance technician.</p>\r\n<p>Most Operational Availability (Ao) and system sustainability problems experienced by the fleet today can be traced to a failure somewhere in the shore-based lifecycle logistics support system. Lack of onboard repair parts (OBRP) supply support is a particularly acute system sustainability problem, but there are also systemic problems with technical manuals, drawings, configuration and other types of engineering technical data. In many cases these technical data problems are the root cause of OBRP support problems, but they are often perceived as a Supply support problem.</p>\r\n<p>ATS uses our unique product lifecycle maintenance solutions to troubleshoot and correct lifecycle integrated logistics support and sustainability problems. Most of our Maintenance Support Group technicians are former Navy technicians who have extensive experience in the operation and maintenance of the full spectrum of shipboard systems. This maintenance-oriented perspective is fundamental to our view of the integrated logistics support world and our maintenance support analysis processes.</p>\r\n<p>We train our maintenance support technicians using our own in-house lifecycle support management training program which we developed from years of hands on experience in all facets of the integrated logistics support system. The end result is an experienced shipboard maintenance technician who is also trained to troubleshoot and repair any element of the Navys integrated logistics support system to make sure the ILS system provides our sailors with the parts, data and tools they need to restore failed systems with minimal delay.</p>\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" align=\"left\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">\r\n<h2>Maintenance &amp; Supportability Analysis</h2>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<h2>Configuration Data Management (CDM)</h2>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>ATS has provided preventative and corrective maintenance support solutions to its customers for over 30 years. Analyzing system failures, maintenance actions and technical data that drive logistics support solutions.&gt; <a title=\"Maintenance and Supportability Analysis\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/our-solutions/lifecycle-support-solutions/maintenance-and-supportability-analysis/\">read more on Maintenance and Supportability</a></td>\r\n<td>CDM is a discipline applied to a Configuration Item for its entire lifecycle - defining system configuration with progressive purification. Effective CDM ensures that the defined user requirements of a Configuration Item are met.&gt; <a title=\"Configuration Data Management\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/our-solutions/lifecycle-support-solutions/configuration-data-management/\">read more on Configuration Data Management</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h2>Product Lifecycle Management (PLM)</h2>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<h2>ILS Support &amp; Training</h2>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>We can deliver a single, authoritative source for product and lifecycle data. Let ATS help you harness the power of Product Lifecycle Management (PLM) processes and systems that can transform your current processes.&gt; <a title=\"Product Lifecycle Management\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/our-solutions/lifecycle-support-solutions/product-lifecycle-management/\">read more on Product Lifecycle Management</a></td>\r\n<td>For over 30 years, ATS has provided our US Navy with the highest level of Integrated Logistics Support providing fleet support, training and assistance during technology insertion.&gt;<a title=\"ILS Support &amp; Training\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/our-solutions/lifecycle-support-solutions/ils-support-training/\">read more on Integrated Logistics Support</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Integrated Logistics Support','','inherit','open','open','','120-revision-v1','','','2014-08-21 21:58:50','2014-08-21 21:58:50','',120,'http://dev.atsid.com/2014/08/21/120-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(566,3,'2014-08-21 21:59:15','2014-08-21 21:59:15','[caption id=\"attachment_249\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"213\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-249\" src=\"http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/lss_index.jpg\" alt=\"Keeping ships ready since 1980\" width=\"213\" height=\"142\" /> Keeping ships ready since 1980[/caption]\r\n<h2>ATS is focused on innovative and sustainable integrated logistic support and lifecycle support solutions.</h2>\r\n<p>For over 30 years, ATS has focused on the development of innovative and sustainable maintenance and lifecycle solutions to product lifecycle system support problems. From the outset, our emphasis has been on finding ways to make the products of the Navys logistics lifecycle support system work for, rather than against, the shipboard maintenance technician.</p>\r\n<p>Most Operational Availability (Ao) and system sustainability problems experienced by the fleet today can be traced to a failure somewhere in the shore-based lifecycle logistics support system. Lack of onboard repair parts (OBRP) supply support is a particularly acute system sustainability problem, but there are also systemic problems with technical manuals, drawings, configuration and other types of engineering technical data. In many cases these technical data problems are the root cause of OBRP support problems, but they are often perceived as a Supply support problem.</p>\r\n<p>ATS uses our unique product lifecycle maintenance solutions to troubleshoot and correct lifecycle integrated logistics support and sustainability problems. Most of our Maintenance Support Group technicians are former Navy technicians who have extensive experience in the operation and maintenance of the full spectrum of shipboard systems. This maintenance-oriented perspective is fundamental to our view of the integrated logistics support world and our maintenance support analysis processes.</p>\r\n<p>We train our maintenance support technicians using our own in-house lifecycle support management training program which we developed from years of hands on experience in all facets of the integrated logistics support system. The end result is an experienced shipboard maintenance technician who is also trained to troubleshoot and repair any element of the Navys integrated logistics support system to make sure the ILS system provides our sailors with the parts, data and tools they need to restore failed systems with minimal delay.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" align=\"left\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">\r\n<h2>Maintenance &amp; Supportability Analysis</h2>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<h2>Configuration Data Management (CDM)</h2>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>ATS has provided preventative and corrective maintenance support solutions to its customers for over 30 years. Analyzing system failures, maintenance actions and technical data that drive logistics support solutions.&gt; <a title=\"Maintenance and Supportability Analysis\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/our-solutions/lifecycle-support-solutions/maintenance-and-supportability-analysis/\">read more on Maintenance and Supportability</a></td>\r\n<td>CDM is a discipline applied to a Configuration Item for its entire lifecycle - defining system configuration with progressive purification. Effective CDM ensures that the defined user requirements of a Configuration Item are met.&gt; <a title=\"Configuration Data Management\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/our-solutions/lifecycle-support-solutions/configuration-data-management/\">read more on Configuration Data Management</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h2>Product Lifecycle Management (PLM)</h2>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<h2>ILS Support &amp; Training</h2>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>We can deliver a single, authoritative source for product and lifecycle data. Let ATS help you harness the power of Product Lifecycle Management (PLM) processes and systems that can transform your current processes.&gt; <a title=\"Product Lifecycle Management\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/our-solutions/lifecycle-support-solutions/product-lifecycle-management/\">read more on Product Lifecycle Management</a></td>\r\n<td>For over 30 years, ATS has provided our US Navy with the highest level of Integrated Logistics Support providing fleet support, training and assistance during technology insertion.&gt;<a title=\"ILS Support &amp; Training\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/our-solutions/lifecycle-support-solutions/ils-support-training/\">read more on Integrated Logistics Support</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Integrated Logistics Support','','inherit','open','open','','120-revision-v1','','','2014-08-21 21:59:15','2014-08-21 21:59:15','',120,'http://dev.atsid.com/2014/08/21/120-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(567,3,'2014-08-21 22:02:12','2014-08-21 22:02:12','<p>ATS has several government-wide acquisition contract vehicles, which are indefinite delivery/indefinite quantity (IDIQ) task order contracts. These flexible contracting arrangements enable us to expedite delivery of our services and systems to clients across the federal government.</p>\r\n<h3>We have the following contract vehicles available for client use:</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a title=\"SeaPort-e\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/contracts-partnerships/contract-vehicles/seaport-e/\">SeaPort-e</a>- the Navy\'s electronic platform for acquiring support services in 22 functional areas including Engineering, Financial Management, and Program Management.</li>\r\n<li><a title=\"GSA Schedule 70\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/contracts-partnerships/contract-vehicles/gsa-schedule-70/\">GSA Schedule 70</a>- IT Schedule 70 is the largest and most widely used acquisition vehicle in the federal government. Schedule 70 is an indefinite delivery indefinite quantity (IDIQ) multiple award schedule, providing direct access to products and services from over 5,000 certified industry partners.</li>\r\n<li>OMNIBUS- supports INSCOMs mission performance to include technical, management, logistics, administrative, information technology, and system support, which directly interfaces with intelligence producers, decision authorities, and intelligence support organizations at INSCOM and other locations as necessary; and (2) provide a source of high quality services to support INSCOM and its MSCs in meeting mission critical requirements.</li>\r\n<li>DIA SITE- Solutions for the Information Technology Enterprise (SITE) contract establishes an acquisition framework for delivering Information Technology services &amp; capabilities that will support the global intelligence Command and Control (C2) assets vital to the security of the United States.</li>\r\n<li>Big Blue- provides technical services for deploying technologies which improve availability, increase reliability, and decrease maintenance and workload requirements for machinery systems and components on naval ships.</li>\r\n<li>MSC- provides technical logistic services in support of COMNAVAIRFOR programs to include Maintenance Support Center (MSC) support and training; assessment support services and CDMD-OA support services.</li>\r\n<li>USDA US Forest Service professional services to perform tasks related to software development, management, enhancement, deployment, maintenance, and support for land management and related business functions of the U.S. Forest Service.</li>\r\n</ul>','Contract Vehicles','','inherit','open','open','','111-revision-v1','','','2014-08-21 22:02:12','2014-08-21 22:02:12','',111,'http://dev.atsid.com/2014/08/21/111-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(568,3,'2014-08-21 22:05:50','2014-08-21 22:05:50','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table border=\"1\" width=\"500\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=