/108-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(572,3,'2014-08-27 17:07:42','2014-08-27 17:07:42','<h3>ATS Provides Fleet Support and Assistance During Technology Insertion</h3>\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">ATS is prepared to provide a variety of program and fleet support services during technology insertion. Following the US Navy guidelines illustrated within the SHIPMAIN process, we plan and coordinate ship grooms, providing data collection, evaluation, training and equipment assistance. We augment the skill and resources of the fleet to provide both onboard and land based technical support to resolve system problems and collect system data to analyze and provide recommendations for system improvements and operation. Also, ATS can provide ILS services to assist clients through the rigorous Regional Maintenance and Modernization Coordination Office (RMMCO) ILS Certification process. Our data experts help you make better decisions to get you working on the ship quicker.</p>\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/meet-ats/contact-us/\">Contact ATS today</a>to learn more.</p>','','','inherit','open','open','','303-revision-v1','','','2014-08-27 17:07:42','2014-08-27 17:07:42','',303,'http://dev.atsid.com/2014/08/27/303-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(573,3,'2014-08-27 17:09:14','2014-08-27 17:09:14','<div id=\"block-views-ats-timeline-block\" class=\"block block-views block-ats-timeline-block block-views-ats-timeline-block odd block-without-title\">\r\n<div class=\"block-inner clearfix\">\r\n<div class=\"content clearfix\">\r\n<div class=\"view view-ats-timeline view-id-ats_timeline view-display-id-block year view-dom-id-aae76e2cee14337206147fa00a415060\">\r\n<div class=\"view-content\">\r\n<div class=\"views-row views-row-1 views-row-odd views-row-first title year-1980 \">\r\n<div class=\"views-field views-field-nothing\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"#\">ATS Founded</a>\r\n<div class=\"details\">\r\n<h3>1980</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">ATS formed by Rick Leenstra, Sr on February 29, 1980</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"views-row views-row-2 views-row-even title year-1980 \">\r\n<div class=\"views-field views-field-nothing\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"#\">Awarded US Navy Contract</a>\r\n<div class=\"details\">\r\n<h3>1980</h3>\r\n<p>Developed Detailed ILO Procedures for NAVSEA</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"views-row views-row-3 views-row-odd title year-1982 \">\r\n<div class=\"views-field views-field-nothing\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"#\">Developed and Implemented ISMS Training </a>\r\n<div class=\"details\">\r\n<h3>1982</h3>\r\n<p>Developed 2-week Integrated Shipboard Maintenance Support (ISMS) mobile training course for work center technicians and implemented same Navy-wide.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"views-row views-row-4 views-row-even title year-1983 \">\r\n<div class=\"views-field views-field-nothing\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"#\">CNM Training</a>\r\n<div class=\"details\">\r\n<h3>1983</h3>\r\n<p>Developed 1-day Flag Officer Logistics Support Product/Problem Awareness training seminar for the Chief of Naval Material (CNM). Conducted same for most fleet/shore-based active duty admirals and senior staff.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"views-row views-row-5 views-row-odd title year-1983 \">\r\n<div class=\"views-field views-field-nothing\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"#\">Developed E-ILO </a>\r\n<div class=\"details\">\r\n<h3>1983</h3>\r\n<p>Developed the Enhanced ILO (E-ILO) process as a means to solve acute configuration/logistics data structure and quality problems which the ILO processes and end products could not solve. Implemented E-ILOs on Pacific Fleet SSN 637/688 class submarines under contract to COMSUBPAC.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"views-row views-row-6 views-row-even title year-1983 \">\r\n<div class=\"views-field views-field-nothing\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"#\">Developed MSC </a>\r\n<div class=\"details\">\r\n<h3>1983</h3>\r\n<p>Developed Maintenance Support Center (MSC) concept for CV/CVNs as an alternative to teaching ISMS to hundreds of work center personnel on large ships. Initially installed and implemented MSCs on Pacific fleet carriers, and later all CV/CVN.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"views-row views-row-7 views-row-odd title year-1992 \">\r\n<div class=\"views-field views-field-nothing\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"#\">Developed CCM </a>\r\n<div class=\"details\">\r\n<h3>1992</h3>\r\n<p>Developed a revolutionary new data management system called the Contiguous Connection Model (CCM) which allowed ATS to model and manage the complex data relationships that exist between the CI that collectively constitute ship systems, their interrelationships and the complex and constantly changing array of engineering, maintenance and logistics technical information (TI) needed to operate, maintain and support the system CI during its life cycle. Submitted Patent application.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"views-row views-row-8 views-row-even title year-1994 \">\r\n<div class=\"views-field views-field-nothing\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"#\">Received first CCM Patent </a>\r\n<div class=\"details\">\r\n<h3>1994</h3>\r\n<p>Received first CCM Patent.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"views-row views-row-9 views-row-odd title year-1998 \">\r\n<div class=\"views-field views-field-nothing\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"#\">ATS awarded Intelligence Community contract </a>\r\n<div class=\"details\">\r\n<h3>1998</h3>\r\n<p>Awarded contract to Army Intelligence and Security Command (INSCOM) to develop and implement CCM-based solutions to data correlation problems.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"views-row views-row-10 views-row-even title year-2005 \">\r\n<div class=\"views-field views-field-nothing\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"#\">ATS opens office in Suffolk, VA </a>\r\n<div class=\"details\">\r\n<h3>2005</h3>\r\n<p>ATS opens office in Suffolk VA</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"views-row views-row-11 views-row-odd title year-2007 \">\r\n<div class=\"views-field views-field-nothing\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"#\">ATS Awarded 2nd Patent </a>\r\n<div class=\"details\">\r\n<h3>2007</h3>\r\n<p>ATS awarded another CCM-based Patent for free text analysis.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"views-row views-row-12 views-row-even title year-2010 \">\r\n<div class=\"views-field views-field-nothing\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"#\">ATS wins Department of Commerce Contract </a>\r\n<div class=\"details\">\r\n<h3>2010</h3>\r\n<p>ATS awarded contract with Department of Commerce and the US Patent and Trademark Office to streamline and automate the Patent End-to-End (PE2E) approval process.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"views-row views-row-13 views-row-odd title year-2011 \">\r\n<div class=\"views-field views-field-nothing\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"#\">ATS Awarded 3rd Patent </a>\r\n<div class=\"details\">\r\n<h3>2011</h3>\r\n<p>ATS awarded it\'s third data-to-decisions patent for relational graph analysis</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"views-row views-row-14 views-row-even title year-2012 \">\r\n<div class=\"views-field views-field-nothing\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"#\">ATS wins 2nd and 3rd Department of Commerce Contract </a>\r\n<div class=\"details\">\r\n<h3>2012</h3>\r\n<p>ATS awarded contract with Department of Commerce and the US Patent and Trademark Office to streamline and automate processes for Trademarks Next Generation (TM-NG) and another contract to develop back-end capabilities with PE2E.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"views-row views-row-15 views-row-odd views-row-last title year-2012 \">\r\n<div class=\"views-field views-field-nothing\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"#\">ATS opens office in Alexandria, VA</a>\r\n<div class=\"details\">\r\n<h3>2012</h3>\r\n<p>Further establishing its DC presence, ATS opens new office in Alexandria, VA</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>ATS is Founded</h3>\r\n<p>Applied Technical Systems was founded in 1980 by Rick Leenstra upon his retirement from the Navy. Prior to his retirement, Leenstra led an effort to implement the Integrated Logistics Overhaul Program (ILO) fleet wide. The program was formally commissioned as a Navy-wide maintenance improvement effort. Leenstra decided to settle down in Washington with his family upon retirement after 23 years of enlisted and commissioned service. Leenstra was asked by a senior NAVSEA official coordinating the ILO efforts to continue implementing the ILO effort as a contractor. Leensstra agreed and formed ATS as a means to work with the Navy to fully implement the ILO program.</p>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_280\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"150\"]<a href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/ADMJackWilliams_1.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-280 size-thumbnail\" src=\"http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/ADMJackWilliams_1-150x142.jpg\" alt=\"ADMJackWilliams_1\" width=\"150\" height=\"142\" /></a> ADM Jack Williams, then Chief of Naval Material teaching COSAL[/caption]\r\n<h3>ATS legacy with Admiral J. G. Jack Williams, USN</h3>\r\n<p>Admiral Jack Williams graduated from the Naval Academy in 1946 and reported to a destroyer as Gun Boss. After completing submarine training he served on USS Pompodon (SS-486) and USS Stickelback (SS-415). He later commanded USS Sterlet (SS-392) and after nuclear power training commanded USS Haddo (SSN-604) and USS Daniel Webster (SSBN-626). After a tour as Director of Training for Naval Reactors, he assumed duties as Force Material Officer (N4) for Commander Submarine Forces, Atlantic. He then took command of Submarine Squadron 16 in Rota, Spain. Upon completion of that tour he was selected for Rear Admiral and subsequently served as Naval Attach to the Turkish Navy. Later he commanded Submarine Group Five in San Diego. Upon promotion to Vice Admiral he served as Deputy Commander, U.S. Pacific Fleet and then as Vice Chief of Naval Operations for Submarine Warfare. In 1981 he was promoted to Admiral and assigned duties as Chief of Naval Material. Admiral Williams retired from the Navy in 1983 and returned to his boyhood home in Illwaco, Washington.</p>\r\n<p>In 1984 he joined ATS as a director and eventually assumed the position of Chairman of the Board, which he held until his unexpected death in 1991. During this period Admiral Williams was instrumental in creating the Naval Undersea Museum in Keyport, served as President of the Northwest Chapter of the Naval Submarine League, and was a key player in helping ATS develop configuration-based lifecycle logistics support solutions for both submarines and surface ships.</p>\r\n<h3>A heritage in solving complex data problems</h3>\r\n<p>Several years before XML became a de facto standard, ATS realized the need for a hierarchical, self-describing, data modeling and storage technology. ATS developed the Contiguous Connection Model (CCM) technology to facilitate rapid information retrieval, enhance data navigation and visualization, and promote knowledge discovery. This patented technology (US Patent #s 5,303,367 and 5,555,409), which was revolutionary for its time, automatically correlates hierarchical data, models it, and stores it in expandable name/value pairs. CCM goes much furtherit creates a complete new hierarchical structure for each and every data point, with the data point as the root. These \"inversions\" are permanently stored and can be intuitively browsed using our powerful visualization tools.</p>\r\n<p>CCM was the pre-cursor to REGGAE, patented under 8,069,188 which is a core component of the ATS Cloud Analytical Platform. REGGAE is an innovative cellular-like data model to describe and relate complex data structures, perform distributed data analytics and find similar data based on like connections and attributes. The invention in this latest patent provides a means to easily discover behaviors and patterns among seemingly unrelated data. For example, a retail store can easily analyze its customer behaviors to determine which products are more suitable for different demographics. There are numerous applications in healthcare, evidence discovery, threat intelligence, etc.</p>','History','','inherit','open','open','','474-revision-v1','','','2014-08-27 17:09:14','2014-08-27 17:09:14','',474,'http://dev.atsid.com/2014/08/27/474-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(574,3,'2014-08-27 17:09:14','2014-08-27 17:09:14','<table width=\"100%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"10\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\">\n\n<strong>Rick Leenstra, Sr., Chairman and Chief Executive Officer</strong>\r\n\r\nSince founding ATS in 1980 upon his retirement from the US Navy, Rick has applied his extensive experience with configuration-based life cycle maintenance support systems for Naval ships and systems to the development of ATS\' technology and service offerings. Rick is the co-inventor of ATS\' patented CCM technology. As Chairman and CEO, Rick leads the ATS Board of Directors and is responsible for corporate oversight and strategic direction. Rick received his BS from Naval Post Graduate School in 1973 and a MBA from Golden Gate University in 1974.</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"220\">\r\n<div align=\"center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://atsid.com/sites/default/files/Rick_Leenstra-13.png\" /></div></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\">\n\n<strong>Bruce MacDonald, President and Chief Operating Officer</strong>\r\n\r\nBruce joined ATS in 2013 as its President and Chief Operating Officer after serving for three years in the Senior Executive Service in the Department of Defense, reporting directly to the Deputy Secretary of Defense. Prior to that, Bruce culminated a 31 year military career serving as the 40th Judge Advocate General of the Navy , becoming the Navys first JAG to attain three-star flag rank. MacDonald graduated from the College of the Holy Cross in 1978 with a Bachelor of Arts degree in English, and entered the Navy in May of that year, serving as an engineering officer on destroyers. He later received his degree of Juris Doctor from California Western School of Law in 1987 and a Master of Laws degree from Harvard Law School in 1992.</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"220\">\r\n<div align=\"center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://atsid.com/sites/default/files/Bruce_MacDonald-13.png\" /></div></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\">\n\n<strong>Felicia King, Chief Financial Officer</strong>\r\n\r\nFelicia joined ATS in 1987 and has guided the company through the financial, contractual and human resource challenges of a growing company. She is responsible for finance, accounting, human resources and facilities. She is a Charter Member of the West Sound Chapter of the National Contract Management Association and has been treasurer of the local chapter since 1991. Felicia holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Accounting from Virginia Tech.</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"220\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://atsid.com/sites/default/files/Felicia_King-13.png\" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\">\n\n<strong>Ken Smith, Chief Information Officer/Chief Technology Officer</strong>\r\n\r\nKen serves as a science and technology advisor to the management teams within ATS andoversees ATS\'s IT and internal research &amp; development efforts, with a focus on cloud computing, Big Data analytics, information visualization, and user experience design.Prior to joining ATS in 2012, Ken led R&amp;D efforts in text mining, information extraction, and data clustering for projects in support of customers within the Army, Air Force, and Naval Research Laboratory. Ken holds a Ph.D. in Physics from The Pennsylvania State University, where he also taught for three years prior to moving to the Washington, DC area.</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"220\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://atsid.com/sites/default/files/Ken_Smith-13.png\" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\">\n\n<strong>Ed Hallda, Vice President, Strategic Development</strong>\r\n\r\nAs both a veteran and contractor, Ed brings more than 20 years of Navy service, technology management and federal business development experience to the fast growing ATS team. Ed is responsible for strategic planning and business development. Prior to joining ATS in 2009, Ed was instrumental in bringing several million dollars of defense contracting to the Kitsap economy. Ed also served as Chief Strategy Officer and Vice President of Engineering &amp; Technology for a public company that formed the largest online mortgage marketplace on the Internet.</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"220\">\r\n<div align=\"center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://atsid.com/sites/default/files/Ed_Hallda-13.png\" /></div></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\">\n\n<strong>Carey B. Kolb, Vice President, Systems Engineering</strong>\r\n\r\nCarey joined ATS in 1996 and is responsible for managing and growing the Systems Engineering business, including the sale of professional services and products to the federal government. Carey holds a Bachelor of Business Administration in Finance from the University of Iowa and a Master of Business Administration in Organizational Behavior from the University of Missouri, Kansas City.</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"220\">\r\n<div align=\"center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://atsid.com/sites/default/files/Leadership-CareyKolb.jpg\" width=\"150\" /></div></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\">\n\n<strong>Doug West, Vice President, Maintenance Support Group</strong>\r\n\r\nDoug joined ATS in 1988 and has been around the U.S. Navy as a maintenance technician, configuration data manager and readiness analyst for 30 years. He is responsible for all aspects of the Maintenance Support Group business operations. A Disabled Navy veteran, Doug also previously served as an executive at AMSEC LLC. He is one of the founding members of the Service Disabled Veteran Owned Small Business (SDVOSB) Council and serves on the Board of Directors (BOD) as Secretary. Doug holds a Bachelor of Business Administration from Almeda University.</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"220\">\r\n<div align=\"center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://atsid.com/sites/default/files/Leadership-DougWest.jpg\" width=\"150\" /></div></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\">\n\n<strong>Jeff Pendry, Director, Systems Engineering</strong>\r\n\r\nJeff is ATSs senior leadership in the D.C. metro area, promoting business development and strategic teaming agreements with industry partners. Jeff joined ATS in 2001 to establish a quality assurance program for ATS and now oversees program management for Systems Engineering. Jeff provides leadership within a variety of IT environments to deliver innovative technology solutions quickly and seamlessly to our customers through an agile framework. As a U.S. Navy veteran and submariner, he adheres to the same principles of honor and integrity and displays this in his commitment to each of his projects and customers. Jeff is a PMI-certified Project Management Professional and a Certified Configuration Manager.</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"220\">\r\n<div align=\"center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://atsid.com/sites/default/files/Leadership-JeffPendry.jpg\" width=\"150\" /></div></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\">\n\n<strong>Dennis Wilkelis, Director, Maintenance Support Group</strong>\r\n\r\nDennis originally joined ATS in 1982 to support tasking developing the Standard PMS Material Identification Guide (SPMIG). Dennis assisted ATS in the development and implementation of the Maintenance Support Center (MSC) program which is still in place today. Being a US Navy veteran and gaining familiarization with US Navy systems has allowed him to be an integral part of the ATS team that continues to support the MSC program; C5ISR assessments; and system sustainment of systems in the fleet. Dennis is responsible for product delivery, continuous process improvements, management of project budgets and cost estimates, and over 30 personnel. He takes an active/hands-on management approach. Dennis also has served as Division Manager at AMSEC LLC.</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"220\">\r\n<div align=\"center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://atsid.com/sites/default/files/Dennis_Wilkelis-13.png\" /></div>\r\n&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\n<br />','Leadership','','inherit','open','open','','74-revision-v1','','','2014-08-27 17:09:14','2014-08-27 17:09:14','',74,'http://dev.atsid.com/2014/08/27/74-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(576,3,'2014-09-10 17:52:09','2014-09-10 17:52:09','<p>Our history of pioneering the development of data-driven, user-centered software has yielded a unique framework of technologies and applications that fulfill a variety of needs for diverse organizations, from traveling sports teams to nuclear power plants. This foundation provides a level of versatility and efficiency, which enables us to bring tailored solutions to market quickly.</p>\r\n<h3>Team Hub</h3>\r\n<p>TeamHub takes the hassle out of event travel planning. It simplifies the coordination and execution of complex itineraries, organizes event-related information from players, and makes it easy to collaborate and manage team activities. <a title=\"Team Hub\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/products/team-hub/\">Learn More...</a></p>\r\n<h3>Crew Atlas</h3>\r\n<p>A comprehensive platform for utilities that provide tools and metrics to help power plants monitor, measure, manage, raise and improve crew performance. <a title=\"Crew Atlas\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/products/crew-atlas/\">Learn More...</a></p>\r\n<h3>Crew Quiz</h3>\r\n<p>Already noted as an industry best practice by site inspectors, Crew Quiz is an online Learning Management System (LMS) that enables a new level of interactive, computer-based training for operators acquiring or maintaining their license.  <a title=\"Crew Quiz\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/products/crew-quiz/\">Learn More...</a></p>\r\n<h3>MSAT</h3>\r\n<p>The Maintenance Supportability Analysis Tool (MSAT) can deliver increased readiness, reduce system downtime, lower operational costs and increase Operational Availability (Ao). ATS was the first company to integrate and validate engineering, maintenance and logistics data and provide the United States Navy with a maintenance sustainment solution that corrects the issues in an effort to improve Operational Availability (Ao). <a title=\"MSAT\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/products/msat-explained/\">Learn More...</a></p>','Solutions','','inherit','open','open','','23-revision-v1','','','2014-09-10 17:52:09','2014-09-10 17:52:09','',23,'http://dev.atsid.com/2014/09/10/23-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(577,3,'2014-09-10 17:53:43','2014-09-10 17:53:43','<aside class=\"alignright\">\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_187\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"213\"]<img class=\"wp-image-187\" src=\"http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/ipad_arcus_search.jpg\" alt=\"Arcus Concept Search interface for the iPad\" width=\"213\" height=\"142\" /> Arcus Concept Search interface for the iPad[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_189\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"213\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-189\" src=\"http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/ipad_arcus_search_results.jpg\" alt=\"Arcus Concept Search results in the iPad\" width=\"213\" height=\"142\" /> Arcus Concept Search results in the iPad[/caption]\r\n\r\n</aside>\r\n<h2>Stop searching, start discovering with Arcus Concept Search data analysis software</h2>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Assists the users in constructing a data query based onthe context of words in the indexed corpus. The important concepts are brought to the users attention by providing visual cues and returning results that are highly relevant  dramatically reducing the time spent in search.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #000000;\">Turn your data analysisinto actionable intelligence</h3>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">While data is usually collected in raw format, such as e-mail or PDF documents, what business and organizations really need to succeed is actionable intelligence. Concept Search data analysis tools enables extracting knowledge from data across an enterprise level business or large organization.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #000000;\">KeyFeatures:</h3>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Arcus Concept Searchs intelligent pre- and post-search capabilities help your team efficiently discover key information from all types of data, including:</p>\r\n<ul style=\"color: #000000;\">\r\n<li><strong>Build Concepts</strong>-return highly relevant search results by choosing from one to five concepts that apply before or after your key term.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Index File Contents</strong> concept indexes are created from website content, documents, and raw text data.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Integrate Easily</strong> services-based architecture makes it easy to integrate discovery into your enterprise-wide processes.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #000000;\">KeyBenefits:</h3>\r\n<ul style=\"color: #000000;\">\r\n<li><strong>Improve Productivity</strong><strong>Arcus Concept Search</strong>saves time and effort by providing visual pre- and post-search filtering of your data.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Discover what youre looking for fast</strong> eliminate multiple searches and sifting through pages of irrelevant results.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Have a holistic view of data</strong> apply concept-aided discovery across e-mail files, attachments, or any type of unstructured document.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Improve reporting accuracy</strong> see all the concepts in all data sets to ensure that youve captured all information needed from your data analysis.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Enhance existing organizational processes</strong> use<strong>Concept Search</strong>by itself or as part of your existing enterprise-wide processes.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Experience the unique power of this technology for yourself. Try the <a href=\"https://demo.atsid.com/cs/\" target=\"_blank\">Arcus Concept Search Demo</a>.</p>\r\n<div id=\"block-system-main\" class=\"block block-system block-main block-system-main even block-without-title\"></div>','Arcus Search','','publish','open','open','','arcus-search','','','2014-10-08 17:10:36','2014-10-08 17:10:36','',23,'http://dev.atsid.com/?page_id=577',5,'page','',0),(578,3,'2014-09-10 17:53:43','2014-09-10 17:53:43','','Arcus Search','','inherit','open','open','','577-revision-v1','','','2014-09-10 17:53:43','2014-09-10 17:53:43','',577,'http://dev.atsid.com/2014/09/10/577-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(579,3,'2014-09-10 17:54:16','2014-09-10 17:54:16','','Smithy','','publish','open','open','','smithy','','','2014-09-10 17:58:14','2014-09-10 17:58:14','',23,'http://dev.atsid.com/?page_id=579',6,'page','',0),(580,3,'2014-09-10 17:54:16','2014-09-10 17:54:16','','Smithy','','inherit','open','open','','579-revision-v1','','','2014-09-10 17:54:16','2014-09-10 17:54:16','',579,'http://dev.atsid.com/2014/09/10/579-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(582,3,'2014-09-10 18:27:57','2014-09-10 18:27:57',' ','','','publish','open','open','','582','','','2014-09-17 22:20:45','2014-09-17 22:20:45','',23,'http://dev.atsid.com/?p=582',14,'nav_menu_item','',0),(583,3,'2014-09-10 18:27:57','2014-09-10 18:27:57',' ','','','publish','open','open','','583','','','2014-09-17 22:20:45','2014-09-17 22:20:45','',23,'http://dev.atsid.com/?p=583',13,'nav_menu_item','',0),(585,3,'2014-10-10 17:56:32','2014-10-10 17:56:32','<h2>Structured &amp; Unstructured Data Analytics with Arcus Cloud Analytical Platform</h2>\n<div id=\"block-system-main\" class=\"block block-system block-main block-system-main even block-without-title\">\n<div class=\"block-inner clearfix\">\n<div class=\"content clearfix\">\n<article id=\"node-basic-page-98\" class=\"node node-basic-page node-published node-not-promoted node-not-sticky author-ebendesign odd clearfix\">\n<div class=\"content clearfix\">\n<div class=\"field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden clearfix\">\n<div class=\"field-items\">\n<div class=\"field-item even\">\n<p>ATS has developed a groundbreaking data analytics platform built on our patented data analytics technology. Our engine ingests and normalizes disparate data sources to create a data structure that facilitates powerful pattern matching and relationship discovery. This service-enabled platform is extensible through various plug-in modules and an open API (based on RESTful web services) that ensure interoperability in a variety of enterprise level business environments. Our patented platform is now available in the cloud, ginalytics at your fingertips.</p>\n<p>This local and cloud based analytics software can assist the user in constructing a data search query based on the context of words in the indexed corpus. The important data is brought to the users attention with easy to understand visual cues. Stop searching and start discovering with data analytics software solutions that make sense.</p>\n<p><a title=\"Arcus Search\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/products/arcus-search/\">Arcus Concept Search</a></p>\n<p>Arcus Concept Search assists the user in constructing a data query based on the context of words in the indexed corpus. The important concepts are brought to the users attention by providing visual cues and returning data results that are highly relevant  dramatically reducing the time spent in search.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</article>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>','Discovery and Decision Support','','inherit','open','open','','195-autosave-v1','','','2014-10-10 17:56:32','2014-10-10 17:56:32','',195,'http://dev.atsid.com/2014/09/16/195-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(586,3,'2014-09-16 20:22:58','2014-09-16 20:22:58','[caption id=\"attachment_196\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"213\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-196\" src=\"http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/1.technology-driven-market-research-conference.jpg\" alt=\"Delivering IT Solutions for a global workforce\" width=\"213\" height=\"142\" /> Delivering IT Solutions for a global workforce[/caption]\r\n\r\n<h3></h3>','Discovery and Decision Support','','inherit','open','open','','195-revision-v1','','','2014-09-16 20:22:58','2014-09-16 20:22:58','',195,'http://dev.atsid.com/2014/09/16/195-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(587,3,'2014-09-16 20:23:31','2014-09-16 20:23:31','<aside class=\"alignright\">\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_342\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"213\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-342\" src=\"http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/qualityassurance-1.jpg\" alt=\"Quality Assurance\" width=\"213\" height=\"142\" /> Quality Assurance[/caption]\r\n\r\n<br /> <br />\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_343\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"213\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-343\" src=\"http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/swe-1.jpg\" alt=\"Collaborative Development\" width=\"213\" height=\"142\" /> Collaborative Development[/caption]\r\n\r\n<br /> <br />\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_344\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"213\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-344\" src=\"http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/whiteboard2-1.jpg\" alt=\"Continuous Engineering\" width=\"213\" height=\"142\" /> Continuous Engineering[/caption]\r\n\r\n</aside>\r\n<h3>Agile Software Development - experts in data</h3>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">ATS is a top software deve