ment Database - Open Architecture (CDMD-OA)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Certifications</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Configuration Data Manager Data - Open Architecture</li>\r\n<li>Acquisition Logistics</li>\r\n<li>Master Training Specialist</li>\r\n<li>Reliability Centered Maintenance (RCM)</li>\r\n<li>Quality Control Inspector</li>\r\n<li>DAU Certified in Acquisition Logistics</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</article>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Lifecycle Support Expertise & Credentials','','inherit','open','open','','313-revision-v1','','','2014-09-16 20:25:37','2014-09-16 20:25:37','',313,'http://dev.atsid.com/2014/09/16/313-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(590,3,'2014-09-16 20:32:58','2014-09-16 20:32:58','<h2>Readiness Improvement for Troubled Systems</h2>\r\n<p>For over 30 years ATS has provided preventative and corrective maintenance support solutions to its customers. ATS is the first company that can show technical data errors between relevant engineering, maintenance and logistics data and provide its customers with a maintenance sustainment solution that corrects the issues that reduce Operational Availability (Ao).</p>\r\n<h2>Maintenance and Supportability Analysis</h2>\r\n<ul style=\"color: #000000;\">\r\n<li>Engineering, Maintenance and Logistic Data interrelation analysis using our Maintenance and SupportabilityAnalysis Tool (MSAT)</li>\r\n<li>System Sustainment Solutions</li>\r\n<li>Maintenance Support Solutions</li>\r\n<li>Maintenance Failure Root Cause Analysis and Solutions</li>\r\n<li>Supply Support Analysis and Solutions</li>\r\n<li>Technical Data Quality Assurance</li>\r\n<li>Acquisition Support Analysis and Solutions</li>\r\n<li>Operational Availability (Ao) Analysis and Solutions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>ATS can help you outline a sustainment strategy/plan to deliver increased readiness and availability.</p>\r\n<h2>Maintenance &amp; Supportability Analysis Tool (MSAT)</h2>\r\n<table style=\"color: #000000;\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>If system readiness and availability are critical to your operation,MSAT can help you deliver increased readiness that reduces system down time, lowers operational costs and increases Ao. <a style=\"color: #8a2216;\" href=\"http://atsid.com/sites/default/files/grid-web.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://atsid.com/sites/default/files/resize/grid-thumb-140x79.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"140\" height=\"79\" /></a><a style=\"color: #8a2216;\" href=\"http://atsid.com/sites/default/files/maint-web.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://atsid.com/sites/default/files/resize/maint-thumb-140x74.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"140\" height=\"74\" /></a> <a style=\"color: #8a2216;\" href=\"http://atsid.com/sites/default/files/supportability-web.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://atsid.com/sites/default/files/resize/supportability-thumb-140x74.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"140\" height=\"74\" /></a></td>\r\n<td><strong>For more information:</strong>email:<a class=\"mailto\" style=\"color: #8a2216;\" href=\"mailto:MSAT Website\">msat@atsid.com</a> phone: 757.483.5959 View:<a style=\"color: #8a2216;\" href=\"http://atsid.com/sites/default/files/MSATFactSheet-email.pdf\">MSAT Fact Sheet</a> Read:<a style=\"color: #8a2216;\" href=\"http://atsid.com/solutions/case-study/maintenance-support-us-navy.html\">MSAT Case Study</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Improve Supportability</strong>- Ingestion and connection ofdisparate failure and support data to identify and fix dataproblems that affect system supportability</li>\r\n<li><strong>Reduce Mean Logistics Delay Time (MLT)</strong>- Identify and fix critical part support problems and put the right parts where they are needed</li>\r\n<li><strong>Monitor Failure Data</strong>- custom dashboards to keep your finger on the pulse of your systems and any data issues affecting their readiness throughout life cycle</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</td>\r\n<td><a style=\"color: #8a2216;\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/meet-ats/contact-us/\"><img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"http://atsid.com/sites/default/files/request-demo2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"45\" /></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Learn more about MSAT as a tool and service or<a style=\"color: #8a2216;\" href=\"http://atsid.com/contact-us?interest=msat-demo\">contact ATS today</a>to learn more about our in-depth Maintenance and Readiness Support Services.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"></p>\r\n<h2>Readiness solutions for both fielded and troubled systems</h2>\r\n<p>The sole function of lifecycle logistics support products is to facilitate efficient and effective execution of system maintenance functions. Consequently, the only way to truly measure the effectiveness of these products (and the processes behind them) is to analyze actual system failures to see how well the logistics support system supported the maintenance action. Failure analysis goes beyond looking at CASREP data. In order to get a true picture of whats failing, logistics support analysts need to take a close look at all maintenance actions to determine exactly what failed, what logistics support was required to restore the system, and whether or not that support was readily identifiable and available to the system technician. Too often there are serious problems with maintenance support, particularly onboard repair parts, but the root cause of these problems is seldom evident to shipboard techniciansthey just learn to live with them. Our technicians, however, are specially trained to troubleshoot and fix these logistics support system problems in much the same way as shipboard technicians are trained to troubleshoot and fix shipboard system problems.</p>\r\n<p>Most onboard logistics support problems can be traced to technical data problems. The lack of integration between engineering, maintenance and logistics support data is a well-known and continuing problem for the Navy. The data that defines the Configuration Items (CI) that collectively constitute ship systems and the seemingly endless array of Technical Information (TI) that define or drive life cycle support requirements for these CI are extremely complex and dynamic. Unfortunately, this interdependent data is typically maintained in disparate data bases with little if any life cycle interaction. Consequently, engineering data soon gets out of sync with maintenance data and the various elements of logistics get out of sync with both engineering and maintenance dataand all get out of sync with the actual system configuration. This lack of data integration and effort creates serious logistics support problems for the fleet, which of course reduces operational readiness. Finding and fixing the root cause of these problems is what ATS does best.</p>\r\n<p>For over 30 years ATS has been dealing with this systemic data integration problemfrom the deck-plate to the SYSCOM level. One of the most important lessons we learned from this experience is the fact that the only true definition of a particular system configuration is the system itself. Moreover, without this solid configuration foundation any attempt to analyze the viability of logistics support is an exercise in futility. Consequently, we begin our analysis by establishing a top-down Configuration Item (CI) breakdown of the system, including a hand-over-hand site sight validation if necessary. We then ingest and link any and all relevant engineering, maintenance and logistics support Technical Information (TI) to these CIwhich of course are the things that fail.</p>\r\n<p>We do this using a unique data correlation system that allows us to integrate this data through a common configuration structure. We call this system MSATMaintenance Supportability Analysis Tool. MSAT has the capability to ingest any type of engineering, maintenance and logistics support data down to the piece part level, and to automatically create and maintain all relevant connections between this data. MSAT also provides the means to automatically show where data disconnects exist and where these disconnects are creating or contributing to deck plate logistics support problems. MSAT also provides the means to fix data errors through automated updates back to source systems. As such, it has the ability to both flush and fix any type of life cycle support data problem.</p>\r\n<p>If system readiness and availability are critical to your operation, or if you can\'t figure out why your system performance is troubled, ATS can help you outline a sustainment strategy to deliver performance.</p>','Maintenance and Supportability Analysis','','inherit','open','open','','260-revision-v1','','','2014-09-16 20:32:58','2014-09-16 20:32:58','',260,'http://dev.atsid.com/2014/09/16/260-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(591,3,'2014-09-16 22:02:05','2014-09-16 22:02:05','<h2>Readiness solutions for both fielded and troubled systems</h2>\n<p>Most onboard logistics support problems can be traced to technical data problems. The lack of integration between engineering, maintenance and logistics support data is a well-known, ongoing issue that reduces Operational Availability (Ao)for the Navy.</p>\n<p>For over 30 years, ATS has provided preventative and corrective maintenance support solutions to its customers. ATS is the first company that can show technical data errors between relevant engineering, maintenance and logistics data and provide its customers with a maintenance sustainment solution that correctsthis systemic data integration problemfrom the deck-plate to the SYSCOM level.</p>\n[caption id=\"attachment_285\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"213\"]<a href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/msc1.png\"><img class=\"wp-image-285 size-full\" src=\"http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/msc1.png\" alt=\"Maintenance Support Center Data Analysis\" width=\"213\" height=\"142\"