TI) to these CIwhich of course are the things that fail.</p>\r\n<p>We do this using a unique data correlation system that allows us to integrate this data through a common configuration structure. We call this system MSATMaintenance Supportability Analysis Tool. MSAT has the capability to ingest any type of engineering, maintenance and logistics support data down to the piece part level, and to automatically create and maintain all relevant connections between this data. MSAT also provides the means to automatically show where data disconnects exist and where these disconnects are creating or contributing to deck plate logistics support problems. MSAT also provides the means to fix data errors through automated updates back to source systems. As such, it has the ability to both flush and fix any type of life cycle support data problem.</p>','Maintenance and Supportability Analysis','','inherit','open','open','','260-revision-v1','','','2014-09-16 20:37:12','2014-09-16 20:37:12','',260,'http://dev.atsid.com/2014/09/16/260-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(593,3,'2014-09-16 20:37:55','2014-09-16 20:37:55','<h2>Readiness solutions for both fielded and troubled systems</h2>\r\n<p>For over 30 years ATS has provided preventative and corrective maintenance support solutions to its customers. ATS is the first company that can show technical data errors between relevant engineering, maintenance and logistics data and provide its customers with a maintenance sustainment solution that corrects the issues that reduce Operational Availability (Ao).</p>\r\n<p>The sole function of lifecycle logistics support products is to facilitate efficient and effective execution of system maintenance functions. Consequently, the only way to truly measure the effectiveness of these products (and the processes behind them) is to analyze actual system failures to see how well the logistics support system supported the maintenance action. Failure analysis goes beyond looking at CASREP data. In or