izes disparate life cycle data to help decision makers drive system performance.</p>\r\n<h3><a title=\"Discovery and Decision Support\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/services/it-services/\">Discovery &amp; Decision Support</a></h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a title=\"Custom Software Development\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/services/software-development/\">Custom Software Development</a></h3>\r\n<p>ATS offers systems integration and custom software development that range from Web portals to data mining applications. Using agile software development we create user-centered designs that will enhance your business workflow.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Services','','inherit','open','open','','25-revision-v1','','','2014-09-17 18:43:02','2014-09-17 18:43:02','',25,'http://dev.atsid.com/2014/09/17/25-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(631,3,'2014-09-17 18:44:55','2014-09-17 18:44:55','<h2>ATS is focused on innovative and sustainable integrated logistics and lifecycle support solutions.</h2>\r\n<p>For over 30 years, ATS has focused on the development of innovative and sustainable maintenance and lifecycle solutions to product lifecycle system support problems. From the outset, our emphasis has been on finding ways to make the products of the Navys logistics lifecycle support system work for, rather than against, the shipboard maintenance technician.</p>\r\n<p>Most Operational Availability (Ao) and system sustainability problems experienced by the fleet today can be traced to a failure somewhere in the shore-based lifecycle logistics support system. Lack of onboard repair parts (OBRP) supply support is a particularly acute system sustainability problem, but there are also systemic problems with technical manuals, drawings, configuration and other types of engineering technical data. In many cases these technical data problems are the root cause of OBRP support problems, but they are often perceived as a Supply support problem.</p>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_249\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"213\"]<a href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/lss_index.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-249 size-full\" src=\"http://dev.atsid.com/wp-content/uploads/lss_index.jpg\" alt=\"Keeping ships ready since 1980\" width=\"213\" height=\"142\" /></a> Keeping ships ready since 1980[/caption]\r\n\r\n<p>ATS uses our unique product lifecycle maintenance solutions to troubleshoot and correct lifecycle integrated logistics support and sustainability problems. Most of our Maintenance Support Group technicians are former Navy technicians who have extensive experience in the operation and maintenance of the full spectrum of shipboard systems. This maintenance-oriented perspective is fundamental to our view of the integrated logistics support world and our maintenance support analysis processes.</p>\r\n<p>We train our maintenance support technicians using our own in-house lifecycle support management training program which we developed from years of hands on experience in all facets of the integrated logistics support system. The end result is an experienced shipboard maintenance technician who is also trained to troubleshoot and repair any element of the Navys integrated logistics support system to make sure the ILS system provides our sailors with the parts, data and tools they need to restore failed systems with minimal delay.</p>\r\n<h3>Maintenance &amp; Supportability Analysis</h3>\r\n<p>ATS has provided preventative and corrective maintenance support solutions to its customers for over 30 years. Analyzing system failures, maintenance actions and technical data that drive logistics support solutions.&gt; <a title=\"Maintenance and Supportability Analysis\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/our-solutions/lifecycle-support-solutions/maintenance-and-supportability-analysis/\">read more on Maintenance and Supportability</a></p>\r\n<h3>Configuration Data Management (CDM)</h3>\r\n<p>CDM is a discipline applied to a Configuration Item for its entire lifecycle - defining system configuration with progressive purification. Effective CDM ensures that the defined user requirements of a Configuration Item are met.&gt; <a title=\"Configuration Data Management\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/our-solutions/lifecycle-support-solutions/configuration-data-management/\">read more on Configuration Data Management</a></p>\r\n<h3>ILS Support &amp; Training</h3>\r\n<p>For over 30 years, ATS has provided our US Navy with the highest level of Integrated Logistics Support providing fleet support, training and assistance during technology insertion.&gt;<a title=\"ILS Support &amp; Training\" href=\"http://dev.atsid.com/our-solutions/lifecycle-support-solutions/ils-support-training/\">read more on Integrated Logistics Support</a></p>','Integrated Logistics Support','','inherit','open','open','','120-revision-v1','','','2014-09-17 18:44:55','2014-09-17 18:44:55','',120,'http://dev.atsid.com/2014/09/17/120-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(632,3,'2014-09-17 18:46:39','2014-09-17 18:46:39','<h2>ATS is focused on innovative and sustainable integrated logistics and lifecycle support solutions.</h2>\r\n<p>For over 30 years, ATS has focused on the development of innovative and sustainable maintenance and lifecycle solutions to product lifecycle system support problems. From the outset, our emphasis has been on finding ways to make the products of the Navys logistics lifecycle support system work for, rather than against, the shipboard maintenance technician.</p>\r\n<p>Most Operational Availability (Ao) and system sustainability problems experienced by the fleet today can be traced to a failure somewhere in the shore-based lifecycle logistics support system. Lack of onboard repair parts (OBRP) supply support is a particularly acute system sustainability problem, but there are also systemic problems with technical manuals, drawings, configuration and other types of engineering technical data. In many cases these technical data problems are the root cause of OBRP suppor